(73, 1, '2011-07-01 13:50:12', '2011-07-01 13:50:12', 'What resembles a toy you used to play with as a child now can hold some of your most important work for the job. Our world is becoming more technologically advanced every day, but that doesn‚Äôt mean we need to part with our childhood and the innovative tyke we used to be. <a href="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-01-at-9.46.28-AM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71" title="Screen shot 2011-07-01 at 9.46.28 AM" src="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-01-at-9.46.28-AM.png" alt="" width="514" height="383" /></a>\n\n<em>Databrick</em> provides handmade high-speed USB 2.0 mini-figures that are compatible with Windows ME/2000, XP, Vista, Windows 7, Mac OS 10.9x and Linus 2.4.\n\nThe USB memory sticks are custom made with LEGO¬Æ brick and knob configurations to produce small characters that carry all of your necessary data. These products are great for all ages and continue to add color and style to the work environment.\n\nHave you ever lost your USB in your bag, purse or briefcase and end up digging around before you finally find it? We have all dealt with that feeling of panic, but with these high-speed LEGO¬Æ USB devices, that can be easily avoided.\n\nThe memory sticks have keychain attachments that can be connected to a key ring, lanyard, zipper on your bag, or even a belt loop. That‚Äôs not all! They are available in transparent colors that allow the USB to light up when in use.\n\nStefan from West Germany, founder of <em>Databrick</em>, creates many themed characters out of LEGOS¬Æ such as pirates, superheroes (Spiderman), movie characters (Darth Vader), even monster trucks and builds themed flash drives. He has very high production standards and uses only professional equipment to ensure that you are provided with the maximum possible quality.\n\n<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lh5nScxvC5g&amp;feature=player_embedded">Databrick on YouTube</a>\n\nAll mini-figures have chip passive cooling devices. Protective caps are incorporated into the design, many serving as the feet for the characters so you wouldn‚Äôt even know that it‚Äôs a flash drive. The figures are also smaller than the average flash drive you would buy in stores.\n\nEach device is personalized and made to your order, so you never receive stock products. With these unique characters, you will not mix up or misplace your USB again.\n\nImpress your friends as you connect a super cool LEGO¬Æ creature to your computer and still have the same amount of space, 4GB-8GB, as the boring, solid-colored flash drives that you used before.\n\nRe-connect with your inner child and make work fun! The artistic possibilities do not stop when you receive your own <em>Databrick</em> USB. You can add on to the USB flash drive and expand with your own LEGOs to personalize your gadgets.<a href="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-01-at-9.45.20-AM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-72" title="Screen shot 2011-07-01 at 9.45.20 AM" src="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-01-at-9.45.20-AM.png" alt="" width="890" height="515" /></a>\n\nPrices range from $69.95 to $249.95 depending on how elaborate your flash drive may be. Delivery takes an estimated 4-5 weeks. Order now at Broodr.com\n\nFind more information about Stefan‚Äôs creations and purchasing procedures at <a href="../../seller/store/85">http://broodr.com/seller/store/85</a>\n\nNote: LEGO¬Æ does not endorse or sponsor these products.', 'The Friday Review: Databrick', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '70-revision', '', '', '2011-07-01 13:50:12', '2011-07-01 13:50:12', '', 70, 'http://broodr.com/blog/?p=73', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
