(100, 1, '2011-04-30 01:51:30', '2011-04-30 01:51:30', 'We are proud to announce that Broodr.com was recently a winner of  a major business competition in New York State, taking home a big first  prize trophy in our division (and some money too!)\r\n\r\nThe prize money we have been awarded will be specifically used to update the site and  make sure Broodr continues to grow at this amazing pace. We hope through your feedback and  continual support we can create some cool new features, provide  customization and support tools, and overall improve the functionality  of the entire site.\r\n\r\nIt''s only been days since we''ve officially gone live so thank you to those who have already uploaded and we look forward to more amazing work from all potential sellers.\r\n\r\nPlease make sure to follow us on Twitter  for more frequent updates: @Broodr\r\n\r\nGeneric catch phrase!\r\n\r\nJason\r\nFounder and CEO', 'Taking home the Gold!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-2', '', '', '2011-04-30 01:51:30', '2011-04-30 01:51:30', '', 12, 'http://broodr.com/blog/?p=100', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(101, 1, '2011-04-26 03:48:06', '2011-04-26 03:48:06', 'Greetings Everyone!\r\n\r\nWe are happy to let you know that Broodr.com  is now done with most of our updates! The checkout system is live so  anyone can purchase items, user may now edit and customize their product  pages/text, and we have upgraded the design (in addition to working out  other bugs).\r\n\r\nIf you haven''t already, please sign up here:\r\n<a href="../../user/adduser" target="_blank">http://broodr.com/user/adduser</a>\r\n\r\nAgain  -- By signing up now, you will become one of the first five hundred  sellers to receive the FREE and UNLIMITED uploading account.. Hurry  quick, because the spots will be going fast - and your uploads will last  a full year.\r\n\r\nIf you''ve already signed up we encourage you to  upload as many items from your inventory as possible. Starting this week  we will begin featuring both items and sellers on the home page and  will start doing blogs/newsletter interviews and highlights for next  month!\r\n\r\nThank you again and we are very excited to have you on  board!¬† If you have any questions, concerns, or thoughts on Broodr,  please feel free to email us directly -- info@broodr.com\r\n\r\nBest,\r\nJason\r\nFounder and CEO', 'Update!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '9-revision-2', '', '', '2011-04-26 03:48:06', '2011-04-26 03:48:06', '', 9, 'http://broodr.com/blog/?p=101', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(102, 1, '2011-04-13 01:37:34', '2011-04-13 01:37:34', 'Hello World Wide Web!\r\n\r\nIf you''re reading this, congratulations - you''ve just stumbled upon  the best kept secret the world has probably just started to hear about.  Broodr.com has just launched (somewhat officially) and although we have a  long road ahead of us (filled with coffee fueled hackathons, invention  road trip competitions, and intense animatronic robot battles)¬† - we''re  happy you''ve decided to come along for the ride. Right now we are  allowing the first 500 people who decide to upload free and unlimited  accounts. After a week or two we will soon open up the check out system  to anyone in the world - so you can begin purchasing items (which is  kind of important too!)\r\n\r\nOur goal with Broodr is to build the best community for entrepreneurs  and inventors of all kind. What are we looking for - the most unique,  coolest, and hardest to find items in the world. So, without further ado  - start uploading your products, browse the marketplace, and share the  site with your friends, family, and even foes.\r\n\r\nThanks and look for some killer updates coming soon!\r\n\r\nJason', 'Welcome to Broodr.com', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-3', '', '', '2011-04-13 01:37:34', '2011-04-13 01:37:34', '', 4, 'http://broodr.com/blog/?p=102', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(103, 2, '2011-07-08 18:38:54', '2011-07-08 18:38:54', 'When the wind is so bitter cold that your face becomes numb, turn to 5 O‚ÄôClock Shadow to keep your noggin warm. ¬†5 O‚ÄôClock Shadow is a company that designs and produces hand knitted ‚Äòbearded facemasks‚Äô. ¬†Perfect for those moments when your coat collar just isn‚Äôt cutting it. ¬†The one of a kind beard‚Äôs are the creation of two women, Tessa and Brea, all the way from Utah. The beards have a cotton-polyester backing for comfort and two elastic straps for stability; making them the perfect accessory for both active and fashionable winter activities.\r\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/FtJ8tUPI-Ek" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n\r\nSo, how does someone come up with this stuff?\r\n\r\n<a href="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/MG_8505_1395198435.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-104" title="_MG_8505_1395198435" src="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/MG_8505_1395198435-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="179" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\nFacial hair has always been a joking topic between Tessa and Brea. Tessa and her husband are ‚Äúhairy‚Äù people according to Brea, since Brea and her bald husband are far from it. These friendly jokes and their curiosity of what it would be like to have a beard are what attracted them to the knitted masks in the first place. Tessa and Brea also both know how to knit, so they began making prototypes to show off with there friends. Being located in an area where cold weather is the norm, they were very dependent on their own head gear and started personally using their own creations, which the local community loved. ¬†Tessa and Brea decided to expand the beard prototypes to include elastic bands, thus making them perfect for outdoor activities like skiing, snowboarding, and hiking.\r\n\r\nThe 5 O‚Äôclock Shadow began to blossom in December of last year and have also gained great attention online. This past winter season was a great kick-off, but now Brea and Tessa are preparing for next season and building up their inventory over the summer, knitting five beards a week. Custom orders can be done in many different colors and sizes for all ages. The recently purchased knitting machine is just the first step. As 5 o‚Äôclock shadow continues to grow, other manufacturing possibilities will be utilized. ¬†So far, local fans like that the beards are homemade.\r\n\r\nIf anyone can make knitting look fun and easy, it is these two creative ladies. Even Conan O‚ÄôBrien even has his own knitted beard - imagine that!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Conan-OBrien_ginger_948002340.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-106" title="Conan-OBrien_ginger_948002340" src="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Conan-OBrien_ginger_948002340-212x300.jpg" alt="" width="212" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\nAfter the beards were made with the natural colors, and a few crazy ones here and there, Tessa and Brea wanted to make a ginger beard. Once they found the yarn, they began knitting. Since they are both huge fans of Conan, this beard was dubbed the Conan O‚ÄôBrien Ginger beard and they even made one just for him, but searched for the right time to send it to him so he would wear it on his show. Tessa and Brea posted their beard and promotional comments on Conan‚Äôs website trying to convince him to wear their handmade beard during his special ‚Äúbeardpocolypse.‚Äù When the time came, Conan did wear a similar knitted beard but it was not the one that Brea and Tessa had made. However, their website did receive more traffic after this look-alike appearance on Conan O‚ÄôBrien.\r\n\r\nYou may be thinking ‚Äòdo these beards even keep my face warm or are they just a funny mask‚Äô?\r\n\r\nWell, in fact the knitted beards are extremely effective. They can be worn with various head gear, and even prevent condensation and fog that other masks create. The polyester handkerchiefs that teens are wearing today do not allow free breathing which makes the inside of the mask wet and cold while fogging up their goggles. The beards are also warm, yet breathable, providing an opening for your mouth. Without question you will see the difference right away when you try one of the beards.\r\n\r\nThe next time you are planning a trip out into the cold, think about buying one of 5 O‚Äôclock Shadow‚Äôs creative beard masks. Not only will you be warm, but your friends will get a kick out of it too!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/MG_6616_410541716.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-107" title="_MG_6616_410541716" src="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/MG_6616_410541716-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\nMake sure to check out 5‚ÄôOclock Shadow‚Äôs Broodr storefront and prepare for winter early!\r\n\r\n<a href="../../seller/store/101">http://broodr.com/seller/store/101</a>', 'The Friday Review: 5 O‚Äôclock Shadow', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-friday-review-5-o%e2%80%99clock-shadow', '', '', '2011-07-08 18:38:54', '2011-07-08 18:38:54', '', 0, 'http://broodr.com/blog/?p=103', 0, 'post', '', 0),
