online. This past winter season was a great kick-off, but now Brea and Tessa are preparing for next season and building up their inventory over the summer, knitting five beards a week. Custom orders can be done in many different colors and sizes for all ages. The recently purchased knitting machine is just the first step. As 5 o‚Äôclock shadow continues to grow, other manufacturing possibilities will be utilized. ¬†So far, local fans like that the beards are homemade.\r\n\r\nIf anyone can make knitting look fun and easy, it is these two creative ladies. Even Conan O‚ÄôBrien even has his own knitted beard - imagine that!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Conan-OBrien_ginger_948002340.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-106" title="Conan-OBrien_ginger_948002340" src="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Conan-OBrien_ginger_948002340-212x300.jpg" alt="" width="212" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\nAfter the beards were made with the natural colors, and a few crazy ones here and there, Tessa and Brea wanted to make a ginger beard. Once they found the yarn, they began knitting. Since they are both huge fans of Conan, this beard was dubbed the Conan O‚ÄôBrien Ginger beard and they even made one just for him, but searched for the right time to send it to him so he would wear it on his show. Tessa and Brea posted their beard and promotional comments on Conan‚Äôs website trying to convince him to wear their handmade beard during his special ‚Äúbeardpocolypse.‚Äù When the time came, Conan did wear a similar knitted beard but it was not the one that Brea and Tessa had made. However, their website did receive more traffic after this look-alike appearance on Conan O‚ÄôBrien.\r\n\r\nYou may be thinking ‚Äòdo these beards even keep my face warm or are they just a funny mask‚Äô?\r\n\r\nWell, in fact the knitted beards are extremely effective. They can be worn with various head gear, and even prevent condensation and fog that other masks create. The polyester handkerchiefs that teens are wearing today do not allow free breathing which makes the inside of the mask wet and cold while fogging up their goggles. The beards are also warm, yet breathable, providing an opening for your mouth. Without question you will see the difference right away when you try one of the beards.\r\n\r\nThe next time you are planning a trip out into the cold, think about buying one of 5 O‚Äôclock Shadow‚Äôs creative beard masks. Not only will you be warm, but your friends will get a kick out of it too!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/MG_6616_410541716.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-107" title="_MG_6616_410541716" src="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/MG_6616_410541716-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\nMake sure to check out 5‚ÄôOclock Shadow‚Äôs Broodr storefront and prepare for winter early!\r\n\r\n<a href="../../seller/store/101">http://broodr.com/seller/store/101</a>', 'The Friday Review: 5 O‚Äôclock Shadow', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '103-revision-11', '', '', '2011-07-08 18:37:27', '2011-07-08 18:37:27', '', 103, 'http://broodr.com/blog/2011/07/08/103-revision-11/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
