(123, 2, '2011-07-15 17:12:18', '2011-07-15 17:12:18', 'When you think of the Netherlands chances are you picture beautiful countryside‚Äôs, friendly people, wonderful food, and of course top-notch electronics and modern design.\n\nWell, one thing is clear - our friends over at Thodio are solidifying this mindset and putting their Dutch brand on the map with a breathtaking approach towards the classic speaker, as well as the iPod accessories genre.\n\n<a href="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/thodio_ibox_xc_teak888.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-121" title="thodio_ibox_xc_teak888" src="http://broodr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/thodio_ibox_xc_teak888-300x198.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="198" /></a>\nCombining both natural and wooden materials such as oak, teak, mahogany, purpleheart ‚Äì wired with technologically advanced speakers and dock accessories, ultimately makes up Thodio‚Äôs gorgeous series of the iBox.\n\nNow you may be wondering (in laymen‚Äôs terms) what the f*%$ is an actual iBox?  As best summarized by Ralph Lauren‚Äôs www.Rugby.com ‚Äì ‚Äúthe Thodio iBox is the best-looking iPod amp ever.‚Äù With a Bose-esque sound quality, easy portability, and unconventional yet gorgeous design, the iBox breaks the mold of iPod docks all over the world.\n\n&nbsp;\n<iframe width="425" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/yIdZXPf11Sc" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\nWith that, there is no question that the iBox‚Äôs beauty lies in its handcrafted nature. Creator Thomas Spaans has managed to produce a ‚Äúsmart looking, solid, handmade option, that stands out from its competitors by virtue of its unconventional design.‚Äù (www.oobject.com)\n\nIt‚Äôs also important to note that each iBox is therefore unique in nature, making the product even more amazing. According to the company, ‚ÄòThe woodwork of the iBox XC was given as much attention and detail as the twin 6.5 inch kevlar coned high quality drivers give to it‚Äôs amazing and powerful sound. The biggest of all Thodio amps is guaranteed to breathe life to any backyard or beach party and exceeds sound/box size ratio expectations, as do all portable Thodio amps.‚Äù\n\nIn terms of the iBox‚Äôs functionality, the system itself couldn‚Äôt be any easier to use ‚Äì simply hook up any of your iPod‚Äôs (or portable music systems) to the dock and you‚Äôre set to begin playing music. The iBox was also specifically designed and crafted in a lightweight fashion, with a rechargeable battery cycle of up to 15 hours, making the device extremely portable.\n\nWithout question the iBox is one of the coolest and most unique products to hit Broodr. Building on the retro designs of the 1950s combined with a post modern hint of recent tech, this one of a kind product from Thodio are certain to blow away anyone who comes in contact with them.\n\nYou can find the iBox on Broodr here: http://broodr.com/product/details/464\nThodio‚Äôs Storefront here: http://broodr.com/seller/store/103', 'The Friday Review: iBox (From Thodio)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '120-revision', '', '', '2011-07-15 17:12:18', '2011-07-15 17:12:18', '', 120, 'http://broodr.com/blog/2011/07/15/120-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
