(30, '', '<p>Copper Gear was created out of a love for steampunk design and the ability to combine the old with the new in unique ways.<br /><br />Our designs try to incorporate the beauty of materials used in the Victorian era, such as wood, copper, brass, and leather, with devices from our era.<br /><br />The devices of old have a completely different feel to them compared to the mass produced plastic "soon to be trash" of today. People used to think of a products lifespan in decades not a few years or even months like we have now. When you buy a "disposable" device there''s no real pride in your purchase because you know it''s going to break or become outdated in a relatively short time.<br /><br />Copper Gear wants to bring back some of that pride by producing equipment and devices that will not only last for many years to come, but also be a joy to use.<br /><br />So what are you waiting for. There''s an alternate reality device waiting to be built for you.</p>\n<p>For more info visit <a href="http://copper-gear.blogspot.com" target="_blank">CopperGear</a></p>', 93, '2011-08-06', 'about', 0),
(31, '', '<p>All Devices are Made-to-Order (once a confirmed order and payment for products is received, products are built). Shipping times may vary depending on device. Please inquire for more info.</p>\n<p>Paypal is the only form of payment excepted.</p>\n<p>All prices are stated in USD</p>\n<p>Shipping:<br />US Priority Mail is used within the United States</p>\n<p>We cannot offer Overnight or Express delivery.</p>\n<p>Shipping prices vary according to product.</p>\n<p>Returns/Exchanges: <br />Since all devices are not made until ordered, they are tested for functionality and quality before shipping. As a result returns/exchanges are not accepted. If a product is damaged during shipping please contact us immediately so we can begin the insurance process with the postal service.</p>', 93, '2011-05-25', 'policy', 0),
