(64, '', '<p>The Jewelers Shop has been one of the largest projects I have ever worked on, and now the doors are open. We specialize in jewelery repair and design while offering a modest collection of finished jewelry.<br /> Stop by if you''re in the area:<br /> <br /> 1029 S Dillard St.<br /> Winter Garden, FL 34787<br /> Phone # 407-615-6218<br /> www.myjewelershop.com<br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: underline;">About the Artist</span></p>\n<p>Nicholas D&rsquo;Amario is an artist of many mediums including photography, jewelry, digital art, and most recently, the art of storytelling. Inspired by childhood memories of growing up in a small New England town; a strong interest in the paranormal; and a passion for all things hidden and unexplored, Nicholas continues to expand his talents.<br /> The works of Nicholas D''Amario grow more vivid with each completed piece. His art has a strong sense of the intangible and shares with the audience the vision of a world seen by all, but remembered by few.</p>', 143, '2011-06-02', 'about', 0),
(65, '', '<div class="row clear">\n<h2>Shipping</h2>\n<p>All items are packaged in a gift box and shipped by USPS Priority Mail with a tracking number. Items will ship within two business days of purchase.</p>\n</div>\n<div class="row clear">\n<h2>Refunds and Exchanges</h2>\n<p>If you are unhappy with your purchase, refunds are acceptable within seven days of the arrival of the piece. Once the returned piece is received, you will be refunded in the same manner that payment was made so long as the piece is in its original condition.</p>\n</div>\n<div class="row clear">\n<h2>Additional Policies and FAQs</h2>\n<p>Have a specific jewelry design you want created? Contact me with the details! I look forward to working with you on the piece you''ve always dreamed of.</p>\n</div>', 143, '2011-06-02', 'policy', 0),
(66, '', '<pre>We here at Recycled Retro do our best to take in the poor antiquated systems of your childhood and transform them into something remarkable! Each piece item we retro fit is carefully disassembled first and cleaned fully after notes are taken on each item. We do our best to utilized every part of each item in one way or another. What we cannot used is recycled. <br /><br />Each item is created at the time of the order. Depending on stock, we may have to order parts from our various contacts. It can take anywhere from one to no more than three weeks for the item to be completed and shipped out due to this, and other things that creep up like day jobs. So please remember this if you need an item by a certain time (ie Christmas, Birthday, etc) and order accordingly.<br /><br />We picked the name Recycled Retro for that very reason. We do our best to provide you with power ups, upgrades, armor, and weapons to take on the next boss. If you have any questions, requests, or comments please feel free to contact us!<br /><br />Each item is your childhood memories of Saturday Mornings, late school nights, talking tactics in class, and collecting 5 pink receipts to get that free game rental!</pre>', 142, '2011-06-07', 'about', 0),
(68, '', '<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Jon Eicher - Specialized Composites, Inc. uses the latest in high performance materials to create unique rugged products for the needs of the digitally mobile world emerging around us. They are the best ruggedized cases made for your IPhone 4 or IPad.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: medium;"> Developing our products in the pedestrian enviroment of New York City gives us a special understanding into the needs and demands of people on the move.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: medium;"> I design and manufacture all our products here in the USA. They are the best of Made in USA .</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: medium;"> Call me at 571-393-0805 with any questions.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: medium;"> We sell globally.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: medium;"> All of our intellectual property is original, is copyrighted, patented and or trademarked. Copyright 2011 All Rights Reserved.</span></p>', 131, '2011-06-11', 'about', 0),
(67, '', '<p>Each item is created at the time of the order. Depending on stock, we may have to order parts from our various contacts. It can take anywhere from one to no more than three weeks for the item to be completed and shipped out due to this, and other things that creep up like day jobs. So please remember this if you need an item by a certain time (ie Christmas, Birthday, etc) and order accordingly.</p>\n<p>Each item is shipped via USPS, the day after the construction is completed and the payment has cleared. Construction can take Two to Three weeks depending on what parts and gear we have in stock. Insurance is the responsibility of the customer, and please let us know of any special requests such as gift wrapping, or shipping to another address.</p>', 142, '2011-06-07', 'policy', 0),
(69, '', '<p><span style="font-size: small;">Joel Scilley is a product designer and woodworker. &nbsp;His company, Audiowood, specializes in handcrafted audio equipment and other home accessories. &nbsp;Joel studied art, design, and architecture in New York and Europe, including an abroad program with Parsons School of Design in Italy. &nbsp;After a decade of working in renovation carpentry in the San Francisco Bay Area, he started Audiowood in 2008, and is focused the innovative and sustainable combination of fine woodworking and precision mechanics. &nbsp;Audiowood is now located in rural Florida, near the state capital of Tallahassee.</span></p>\n<p><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span class="Apple-style-span">Audiowood designs have been featured in The New York Times, California Home and Design, Metropolitan Home, Zink!, Velvet (Italy), and on BoingBoing, Coolhunting, Thrillist, Daily Candy, Notcot, and 1800recycling.</span></span></span></p>\n<p><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span class="Apple-style-span"><br /></span></span></span></p>', 146, '2011-06-14', 'about', 0),
(70, '', '<p><span style="font-size: small;">Audiowood is devoted to utterly professional customer service. &nbsp;If something is wrong, we will make it right.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Unless otherwise specified, all Audiowood products come with a 1 year warranty.</span></p>', 146, '2011-06-13', 'policy', 0),
(71, '', '<div class="static-content clear-block" style="text-align: center;">\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Your goal is to slice. Our goal is to help you do it with style, beauty, and grace. That&rsquo;s why every Slice&trade; cutting tool is a passionate celebration of bold design and extraordinary function.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;">We collaborate with some of the most innovative designers on the planet. They take everyday objects - scissors, safety knives, letter openers, ceramic knives, <a href="http://www.sliceproducts.com/product/safety-cutter">Safety Cutters</a> - and rethink them. How can a safety cutter or a pair of <a href="hhttp://www.sliceproducts.com/product/stainless-steel-scissors">scissors</a> be better? What can we do to reinvent a <a href="http://www.sliceproducts.com/product/box-cutter-0">Box Cutter</a> so it is easier to use? How can we reconfigure beauty tools to make them into works of art?</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;">The result is a collection of award-winning, innovative cutting tools for your home, office, and school that will help you slice in style and inspire you to create great works of art yourself.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Slice was founded in 2008 by TJ Scimone as a way to help fund long-term care for his son, Alex, who is autistic. A minimum of 1% of all Slice product sales is donated to help <a href="http://www.sliceproducts.com/content/one-percent-autism">fund autism research</a>. By purchasing our products, you&rsquo;re helping to find a cure for the millions of children and their families who live with autism every day.</span></p>\n</div>', 122, '2011-06-16', 'about', 0),
(72, '', '<p><span style="font-size: small;">Slice&trade; ships exclusively with FedEx to make sure your order gets to you on time. We offer a variety of shipping methods to meet your needs, including:</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Standard Ground Shipping: delivers within 5 to 8 business days after shipping</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - 2-Day Shipping: delivers within 2 business days after shipping</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Standard Overnight : delivers within 1 business day after shipping</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Priority Overnight : delivers the next morning</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Shipping costs</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> Shipping costs are calculated and displayed before you complete your order. You can also see shipping costs on the Order Acknowledgment email and on online. If you order multiple items, you may receive separate shipments. You will receive a Shipment Notification email for each shipment with tracking information, if available. Shipping fees for the entire order will be charged when your first item is shipped.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Signature on Delivery</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> Once your order has prepared for shipment or has shipped, we are unable to change the shipping address. Most of our shipments contain valuable items, so our carriers are required to obtain a signature upon delivery. Please note that the carrier makes three delivery attempts before returning your package to Slice, Inc. Anyone over the age of eighteen at the designated shipping address can sign for the package. You can also sign to release your shipment to your address, an immediate neighbor, or a building manager.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Shipping Locations &amp; Restrictions</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> The Slice Online Store ships items only within the United States and Canada. No shipments can be made to PO Box addresses, United States territories, or addresses outside of the United States or Canada. The Slice Online Store does not support shipping items in a single order to multiple shipping addresses. To ship items to an additional address, please place a new order.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Shipping Outside the U.S. and Canada</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> If you would like to purchase or ship Slice products outside the U.S. or Canada, please email <a href="mailto:service@sliceproducts.com">service@sliceproducts.com</a> and we will do our best to accommodate your request.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Challenges With Your Shipment</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> If you paid for expedited shipping and did not receive your package on time, or if you received the wrong product or if it was damaged during shipping. please email <a href="mailto:service@sliceproducts.com">service@sliceproducts.com</a>. Our goal is to make sure you are completely satisfied with your order.</span></p>', 122, '2011-06-16', 'policy', 0),
(73, '', '<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Exovault</strong> is an artist-run company; we provide the kind of low volume, high-quality product that can appeal to a small and specific part of the population- like you. &nbsp;We are irritated by so many high volume, &nbsp;mass-produced products that must lose their individuality and integrity in order to appeal to an increasingly wide and thus inherently bland demographic. <strong>EXOvault</strong> cases are made in our studios in Brooklyn, NY- from design, to proto-type to the final hand-finished product, we take steps to stand apart from the rest in our level of craftsmanship, our choice of quality materials and our dedication and attention to detail. Our design is not intended to appeal to all, it is interned to appeal to the few with a higher standard. Our goal is to remain small and individual. We stand behind our cases, and want you to enjoy them as much as we do! A lot of people have iPhones- only a few have the protection of an <strong>EXOvault</strong> case. </span></p>', 148, '2011-06-16', 'about', 0),
(74, '', '<p>We make all of our cases according to order and design and produce them in house. Quality and attention to detail takes time! Please be patient while we produce your case as we are working as quickly and as carefully as possible. Most orders will ship out within one week. If you have questions or concerns regarding your EXOvault case order please contact us via email at exovault@gmail.com.</p>', 148, '2011-06-16', 'policy', 0),
