(77, '', '<div id="biography">\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Dan McVeagh is an independent designer and inventor from Pittsburgh, PA. I am passionate about emerging technologies including multi-touch interaction and surface computing. I studied Civil Engineering and Information Technology in my home town where I live and work. I like to work in my lab creating proto-types with clay and Sugru a silicone based modeling clay. Designed in 3D mostly with Sketch-up and rendered using Render-in engine, Slinkables were created after finding a need for a device that brings technology products closer together.</span></p>\n</div>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><a class="popup" href="http://slinkable.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Slinkable.com</a></span></p>', 158, '2011-07-07', 'about', 0),
(78, '', '<p><span style="font-size: small;">I''m Sara, handmade enthusiast and nerd herd member. </span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> I''ve always been drawn to the creative process and I''ve tinkered with many forms of it over the years. I''ve gone from drawing to design, decoupage to origami, crochet to coding. My primary areas of interest have always been paper crafts and graphic design.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> In my spare time I enjoy all things geek, especially video games, computers, technology, gadgets, astronomy, philosophy, and scientific explorations.</span></p>', 100, '2011-07-08', 'about', 0),
(79, '', '<p><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Payment</strong></span></p>\n<p><br /> <span style="font-size: large;">Accepted Payment Methods</span><br /> <br /> &bull; <span style="font-size: small;">PayPal</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> &bull; Major Credit Cards via PayPal (Visa, MasterCard, Discover, American Express)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> &bull; PayPal eCheck (eCheck purchases will ship after payment has cleared, which usually takes 4-10 business days.)</span><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: large;"> When Payment is Due</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> Payment is due in full when you place your order. Checkout will require payment before your order is finalized.</span><br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><span style="font-size: large;"> Canceling a Sale</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> If you are unable to complete your purchase please contact me as soon as possible so I can take care of canceling the transaction.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Shipping</strong></span></p>\n<p><br /><span style="font-size: large;"> When I Ship</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> &bull; Daily Monday through Friday</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> &bull; Within 2 business days once payment is complete</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> Please note that I don''t ship on nationally recognized postal holidays or weekends.</span><br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><span style="font-size: large;"> Shipping Services</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> I ship worldwide via United States Postal Service First Class Mail (unless otherwise noted).</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> I can easily upgrade your parcel to USPS Priority or Express mail if you prefer. Please include a note during checkout or contact me so I can adjust your postage accordingly. For domestic (US) mail upgrades, please add $3.25 for Priority mail and $17.50 for Express mail. Expedited International mail upgrades tend to be quite expensive, so please contact me for pricing.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> If your purchase is a gift, I can ship directly to your recipient. I won''t include details of the transaction so your gift''s cost will not be revealed unless I''m required to disclose it on a customs form. I can also include a personalized note from you (just let me know during checkout).</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> Please note that international shipments may incur fees or duties when processed by customs. These charges are not included in my costs and must be paid by the buyer upon receipt. I''m required to fully disclose the value of all international mail on the package''s exterior.</span><br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><span style="font-size: large;"> I Combine Shipping!</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> I gladly combine shipping for multiple items that you purchase and pay for at the same time. Most combined rates should automatically be calculated during checkout. If there is an error during checkout, I will correct your invoice and issue a refund for the overcharge.</span><br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><span style="font-size: large;"> How I Ship</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> I take great care to ensure the safe arrival of your parcel. I secure packages as best I can to prevent tampering and damage from the elements. I use sturdy mailers that are tear/moisture resistant and carefully bubble wrap items that require padding. Shipping labels are printed directly from your order information using professional postage software to ensure 100% accuracy.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> I will notify you once your purchase has been shipped. If your shipment is domestic (an address within the United States), I will provide your parcel''s eDelivery Confirmation number.</span><br /> <br /> <br /><span style="font-size: large;"> International Shipping</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> I''m happy to ship orders worldwide. Please keep the following in mind regarding international mail:</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> &bull; Parcel transit times can vary greatly and cannot be guaranteed. Your parcel may take longer to arrive if delayed by customs processing. Please keep this in mind when making time sensitive purchases. International parcels cannot be tracked. </span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> &bull; International shipments may incur fees or duties when processed by customs. These charges are not included in my costs and must be paid by the buyer upon receipt. I''m required to fully disclose the value of all international mail on the package''s exterior.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Refunds and Exchanges</strong></span></p>\n<p><br /><span style="font-size: large;"> Return Policy</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> I''m committed to 100% buyer satisfaction. I want you to be completely happy with your purchase. If there is a problem with your order please contact me within 7 days of receipt. I will work with you to appropriately correct the issue.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> Refunds are issued to the original purchaser via the same payment method originally used. Exchanges are offered for a listing of equal value and are shipped to the same address as the original purchase.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> Please note that custom and private sales may not be subject to my normal return and exchange policy.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Additional Policies and FAQs</strong></span></p>\n<p><br /><span style="font-size: large;"> Quality Commitment</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> Quality control is very important to me. I lovingly prepare my handmade accessories from scratch using quality ingredients. I want to do all I can to ensure a long, enjoyable life for my creations. If you have questions about any of the materials used to produce my items, please feel free to contact me.</span><br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><span style="font-size: large;"> Custom Orders</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> Perhaps you need a larger quantity of something that''s already listed, or want to mix and match between listings. Maybe you&rsquo;re seeking something not yet in my store, like a custom one-of-a-kind item. No matter what you''re looking for, please contact me. I''d love to create something unique just for you!</span></p>', 100, '2011-07-08', 'policy', 0),
(80, '', '<h2><span style="font-size: small;">Who is Pad&amp;Quill?</span></h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">A family company based in Minneapolis who loves God, our kids, entrepreneurship and our dog&hellip;in that order (sorry pooch). We are technology geeks who love to read, surf the web and are clearly in the &lsquo;early adopter&rsquo; classification for cool stuff. Our mission is to deliver the most beautiful, high quality, hand made bookbindery cases for a full array of amazing devices.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2><span style="font-size: small;">How do I care for my new case?</span></h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Your Pad&amp;Quill case will wear like an old book if it is treated like the device inside, with common sense care.&nbsp;We ask that the case is not left in hot cars, exposed to extremely cold temperatures,&nbsp;used as a dog catching toy, exposed to a toddler''s curiosity or any other activity that the device it carries could not live through. For cleaning, use a slightly damp cloth over the binding material. The birch wood is finished with an extremely hard Eco friendly water based urethane.&nbsp; For any reason you spill or stain the wood simply use a damp cloth to clean the affected area. Over time binding material will wear like a favorite book, especially on the edges and in the creases....we love that!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2><span style="font-size: small;">What is your warranty?</span></h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Our cases use the highest quality craftsmanship supplied with natural wood products and artistic binding material. Our cases smell like a real hand made book! There will be imperfections in the wood and variations of pattern with the bindery material that are part of a hand crafted product. Please note that with premium book bindery materials the interior creases will wear over time, depending on usage.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> We warranty the cases from manufacturing defect for 14 days from delivery. If you receive your case and there are clear manufacturing related defects, please do not hesitate to contact us for a full refund or replacement.&nbsp;</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> The Pad&amp;Quill case is a rugged, solid built case that offers significant protection for your device. Although we cannot warranty protection of your device, we are confident you will love the security our case provides.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2><span style="font-size: small;">What about returns?</span></h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">You may cancel your order within 3 business days of ordering the product and we will refund your money.&nbsp; We accept returns within 7 days from delivery and will credit you as long as the case is returned undamaged and in new condition. Please send returns to Pad&amp;Quill,&nbsp;2400 N. 2nd St., Minneapolis, MN 55411.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">We at Pad&amp;Quill love to hear encouraging comments regarding your experience with our beautiful cases. Thank you for helping us make the case for books!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Brian &amp; Kari</span></p>', 161, '2011-07-15', 'about', 0),
(81, '', '<h2><span style="font-size: small;">What about returns?</span></h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">You may cancel your order within 3 business days of ordering the product and we will refund your money.&nbsp; We accept returns within 7 days from delivery and will credit you as long as the case is returned undamaged and in new condition. Please send returns to Pad&amp;Quill,&nbsp;2400 N. 2nd St., Minneapolis, MN 55411. <br /></span></p>', 161, '2011-07-15', 'policy', 0),
