(60, 155, 'Kork - Natural Protection for iPad 1', 49.90, 0.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Px2sHBiUk6U&feature=youtu.be', 'ipad,case,kork,protection,design', 50, '<div class="section-content">  Special Broodr Price of $49.90, usually $ 72. Limited only to 50 Korks. <br /><br /><br /> FEATURES and TECH SPECS <br /><br /><br /> - Recycled and Recyclable Natural Cork <br /><br /><br /> - Easy access to all Buttons and Inputs <br /><br /><br /> - Ergonomic Natural Shape and Feel <br /><br /><br /> - Angled Audio Output for Front Projected Sound <br /><br /><br /> - Larger Dock Connection Extra Space for Connectors <br /><br /><br /> - Extra Space for Bigger Jack Input <br /><br /><br /> - Angled Mic. Wall for User Directed Sound Caption <br /><br /><br /> - Very Light Weight <br /><br /><br /> GREAT CAN be EVEN BETTER <br /><br /><br /> The iPad is a masterpiece of engineering, we have no doubt about that. <br /><br /> The Design is beautiful too. <br /><br /> It¬¥s the ergonomics and practicality that was the driving force in the Kork¬¥s Design process. <br /><br /> We can all agree that when using the iPad, you engage in a new and more intimate experience, <br /><br />  whether you¬¥re browsing, gaming or using Apps. <br /><br /> This was the area we wanted to explore and enhance. <br /><br /><br /><br /> LIKE PUTTING on A PAIR OF SLIPPERS <br /><br /><br />  The iPad is mainly used in the comfort of your home, either sitting at the table or relaxing on the sofa. <br /><br /> When in use on the go, you are usually seated somehow as well. <br /><br /> This is why The Kork is the iPads perfect companion, it has a thicker, more ergonomic grip when you hold it. <br /><br /> Lets face it, our hands are not flat, they need something to hold onto. <br /><br /> The Kork does exactly this, the position of your hands when holding is a natural position causing less strain and stress. <br /> It fits snugly into your hand and won‚Äôt slip when your hands are sweaty. <br /><br /><br /> "The Kork‚Ñ¢ is a eco-friendly, sustainable and unique piece of Design. <br /><br /> Made from 100% natural leftover cork, it is molded into a uni-body shell that holds the iPad in place. <br /><br /> Great protection while looking smart, and is ergonomically designed to fit perfectly in your hand, <br /> with a natural grip and feel. Practical, easy to use and very comfortable. <br /><br /> Very light weight, with easy access to all buttons and inputs. <br /><br /> Nothing has been left to chance, even the Korks walls are angled to project the sound towards the user. <br /><br /> The Kork‚Ñ¢ is a fine blend of Technology and Nature." <br /><br /><br /> SPACE AND ANGLES for BETTER USE <br /><br /> The Kork has an angled wall to bounce the iPads speaker audio forward toward the user. <br /><br /> The same happens with the built in microphone, it is also angled to help eliminate background noise and enhance <br />  voice capture. <br /><br /> We have allowed extra space for larger jack input and pin connector <br /><br /> so you wont have to remove the case to access audio in/out or sticking the camera kit adapters on. <br /><br /> Same goes for all the buttons, the Korks wall is organically curved for easy access. <br /><br /><br /><br /> "With the kork slipped on your iPad, there is really no need for kickstands or other attach-ments. <br /><br /> This is because cork has the great natural ability to no-slip grip onto almost any surface you put it on. <br /><br /> Stands are also limited position-wise, with the Kork, you have the freedom to prop it up just right, no stands <br /> attached." <br /><br /><br /><br /> ECO-FRIENDLY by DESIGN  <br /><br /><br /> We have taken our time to develop and test this great new iPad Case. <br /><br /> It not only offers great protection but also gives the iPad a more ergonomic grip and natural feel. <br /><br /> The perfect combination of Technology and Nature. <br /><br /> Our design differs in many ways from those currently available. <br /><br /> It is made from 100% natural leftover cork, <br /><br /> ground into cork granules that are then molded into a uni-body shell with a binding agent, <br /><br /> the same that Wine-makers swear by across the globe. <br /><br /><br /> "We have chosen to work with Cork as a material because of its impermeability, buoyancy, elasticity, fire <br /><br /> resistance, eco-friendliness and sustainability. " </div>', 1, '2011-04-14', 83, 8, ',,,', 'Please allow for 2 weeks delivery time.', 1, 0),
