(62, 239, 'FLOW G1.55', 1398.55, 25.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=onpbVaaon30', 'flow,gizmoforyou,android,linux,open source', 5, '<p>This is the Second version of our FLOW Gizmo and it has been altered quite a bit. As you can see from the image it has been redesigned not only from the inside but also the exterior enclosure has changed. With a nice colorization and a rigid enclosure it really is the best development or not device to use or to work with.&nbsp; We have put many hours into the design of this device to eliminate any errors or requests from users and have added many usefull features which were not included before in the Gizmo.<br /><br /><strong>Specifications and features</strong><br /><br />- 480 x 640 pixels 3.7" LCD with a resistive Touch- Screen<br />- HDMI Out through the 24pin connector<br />- 3mp Camera<br />- ZigBit 2.4GHz RF Transceiver (Internal Antenna)<br />- UC864-G Module (GSM-GPS-GPRS-UMTS with all antennas included)<br />- Mono Speaker for Audio<br />- Stereo Headphone Jack 3.5mm<br />- Triple Axis Accelerometer<br />- Digital Compass<br />- Battery Monitoring &amp; Status (Temperature, Capacity and other info)<br />- 1500mA Li-Po Battery in an Ultra Slim Profile of 3.2mm<br />- 400mA Fast Charger (only though power supply)<br />- Vibrator Motor<br />- Device is supplied with Overo Fire<br />- 2 x General Purpose buttons (By default assigned to Home &amp; Back in Android)<br />- Android Eclair Operating environment (at the time of his writing)<br />- External dimensions are: 116mm x 68mm x 18mm<br />- Simple and rigid enclosure with internal PCB support as well as support for all internal components.<br />- Enclosure is Colorized as seen on the picture above. (Custom colorization for larger quantities is available)<br />- 6 Layer 1.2mm thick PCB Design with carefully routed tracks and shielded with Power planes.<br />- Customizable internal switches for envelopment and debugging.<br /><br /><strong>ZigBit 900MHz Transceiver Information</strong><br /><br />ZigBit&trade; 900 is an ultra-compact, extended range, low-power, high-sensitivity 784/868/915 MHz<br />IEEE 802.15.4/ZigBee&reg; OEM module, based on the innovative Atmel&rsquo;s mixed-signal hardware platform.<br />It is designed for wireless sensing, control and data acquisition applications. ZigBit modules eliminate<br />the need for costly and time-consuming RF development, and shortens time to market for a wide range<br />of wireless applications.<br /><br />Please note that this feature comes by default on the FLOW G1.5<br /><br /><strong>UC864-G General Information</strong><br /><br />The UC864-G is a 3.5G wireless data module designed to be fully compatible with Telit''s GSM/GPRS and CDMA products in the compact, unified form factor family. This enables integrators and developers to design their applications once and take advantage of the truly global coverage and service flexibility afforded by the combination of the two most prevalent cellular technologies worldwide.<br /><br />The UC864-G was designed for applications requiring global portability afforded by a radio structure comprised of quad-band support to GSM/GPRS/EDGE and tri-band UMTS/HSDPA. With its ultra-compact design, and extended operating temperature range, the Telit UC864-G is the perfect platform for medium-to-high-volume m2m applications and mobile data and computing devices.<br /><br />Additional features such as, integrated TCP/IP and UDP, integrated full 12-channel high sensitivity GPS functionality for indoor fixes and simultaneous GPS with voice &amp; data, one DAC channel and a three channel ADC provide extended functionality, adding value to the end application without adding cost.<br /><br /><strong>Overo Fire Specifications</strong><br /><br />Processor:&nbsp; OMAP 3530 Applications Processor with ARM Cortex-A8 CPU, a C64x+ digital signal processor&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (DSP) core, and the POWERVR SGX for 2D and 3D graphics acceleration<br />Clock(MHz): 600 MHz<br />Performance: Up to 1200 Dhrystone MIPS<br />Memory:&nbsp; 256MB RAM 256MB Flash<br />Features: - on-board microSD card slot - I2C, PWM lines (6), A/D (6), 1-wire, UART, SPI, Camera in, Extra MMC lines - Headset, Microphone, backup battery, - USB OTG signals, USB HS Host (Please consult the Forum or check out the schematics to see how these signals are connected to FLOW G1.5)<br />Wireless Communication: 802.11(g) and Bluetooth&reg;<br /><br />Please have in mind that the 27pin FLEX cable is included and installed to take advantage of the Camera feature of the device.<br /><br /><strong>Additional Information</strong><br /><br />You can find more information about this Gizmo in our Projects and Blog sections of the website as well as the Forums at <strong><a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.com">our website</a></strong> , where we have descriptions and the workflow we went through for finishing this device.</p>', 1, '2011-04-26', 92, 15, ',distributor,funding,promotion', '<p>The product is shipped by EMS data post. It is ensured and arrives in approximately 10 - 15 working days.</p>', 1, 0),
