(88, 160, 'WiFi Linux Wall-Plug', 710.00, 30.00, '', 'gizmoforyou,wifi,linux,camera,computer', 5, '<p>This Gizmo (as many others in our shop) was suggested by one of our member. The main idea for this device is to have 2 or more of these Gizmos plugged into different areas of the house and through Gestures or sound commands to be able to interact with home appliances or other devices.<br /><br />Although the above idea was the main reason we created this Gizmo, it doesn''t mean that it should be limited to this application. Based on the features of the device, the applications are endless and the only barrier is your own imagination.<br /><br /><strong>Main Features</strong><br /><br />-Self Contained Internal Power Supply using the Wall Plug operational at 120v - 230v AC.<br />-2 x 3MP Cameras - OV3640 (Gumstix 27pin Flex Ribbon included)<br />-Digital Compass For Orientation - HMC6352<br />-USB Port for Programming &amp; Debugging<br />-Internal Speaker for Audio<br />-2 x High End Microphone Preamps for high Audio Sensitivity (2 x Internal Microphones)<br />-4 x RGB LED''s for Status indication<br />-Bluetooth &amp; WiFi antennas included as on the image<br />-Dimensions: (L) 104.369 x (W) 56.718 x (H)&nbsp; 38.481mm<br /><br /><strong>Overo Air Features</strong><br /><br />Overo Air a tiny, ARM Cortex-A8 OMAP3503 based computer-on-module that communicates via 802.11g and Bluetooth, is low cost, high performance and production ready. Network connect your product and manage it wirelessly, while the Cortex-A8 delivers the performance you crave.<br /><br /><br />-Processor: OMAP 3503 Application Processor with ARM Cortex-A8 CPU<br />-Clock: 600MHz<br />-Memory: 256MB Flash &amp; 256MB Ram<br />-General IO''s: on-board microSD card slot, I2C, PWM lines (6), A/D (6), 1-wire, UART, SPI, Camera in, Extra -MMC lines, Headset, Microphone, backup battery, USB OTG signals, USB HS Host<br />-Wireless Communications: 802.11(g) and Bluetooth<br />-Dimensions: 17mm x 58mm x 4.2mm<br /><br /><strong>Additional Information</strong><br /><br />You can find more information about this Gizmo in our Projects and Blog sections of the website as well as the Forums at <a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.com"><strong>our website</strong></a> , where we have descriptions and the workflow we went through for finishing this device.</p>', 1, '2011-04-26', 92, 15, ',distributor,funding,promotion', '<p>The product is shipped by EMS data post. It is ensured and arrives in approximately 10 - 15 working days.</p>', 1, 0),
(89, 384, 'Ares Gaming Platform', 810.00, 30.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L1DUm0csyJw', 'gaming,gizmoforyou,handheld,pda,game', 5, '<p>As most of our Gizmos, this one was a wish from one of our members. The main idea was to have an Open Source gaming platform for the community. Based on the Verdex series of platforms from Gumstix this is a truly powerful solution with many cool features and applications. You can select which platform you would like to use for the device or if you would like to use your own Verdex platform.<br /><br /><strong>Main Features</strong><br /><br />-4.3" diagonal screen. WQVGA (480x272 pixels)<br />-Resistive Touch screen panel<br />-microSD Card Slot<br />-Stereo Speakers<br />-Analog Thumb-Stick (similar to the one used on the PSP)<br />-6 General purpose Buttons which are easily pressable and ideal for fast responce while playing<br />-USB Interface for development<br />-2200mA Li-Po Battery<br />-Onboard Battery charger<br />-Vibrator for Shock or other application<br />-Internal JTAG connector for development and debugging.</p>\n<p><strong>Gumstix Verdex Pro XL6P</strong><br /><br />-Processor - Marvell PXA270 with XScale<br />-Speed - 600 MHz<br />-RAM - 128MB<br />-FLASH - 32MB<br /><br /><strong>Additional Information</strong><br /><br />You can find more information about this Gizmo in our Projects and Blog sections of the website as well as the Forums at <strong><a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.com">our website</a></strong> , where we have descriptions and the workflow we went through for finishing this device. Please have in mind that this product comes by default with the Verdex XLV6 board and Power adaptor.</p>', 1, '2011-04-26', 92, 15, ',distributor,funding,promotion', '<p>The product is shipped by EMS data post. It is ensured and arrives in approximately 10 - 15 working days.</p>', 1, 1),
(90, 143, 'Camera Trigger', 325.00, 30.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I9-qR1iXwjc', 'photography,camera,trigger,photo,gizmoforyou', 5, '<p>This Gizmo was created based on a wish that a member on our community made. The idea already existed for a device that could trigger a High Resolution Camera based on settings or sensors. With this Gizmo you can pretty much do everything you ever wanted with a Camera or multiple cameras, Flash units and sensors. Set up your scene as you want it, adjust the settings and sensors you need and simply wait for the device to do the rest. There are endless applications for this device and the only limit is your imagination. Use it for taking photos of Lightning as it strikes based on the sound or on the actual light emitted. Take photos of animals as they walk by without even touching the device. Laser Trigger or motion trigger the camera or even leave it for a long period of time and take pictures of a flower as it opens at sunrise and closes at sunset with intervals of your choosing. We have growing collection of sensors for this unit and always glad to make even more based on member requests. Since the software and hardware of this Gizmo (as any Gizmo we make) is Open Source, you can simply tell us a new feature or menu that you need and we shall add it for you. Plug it with a USB cable to your PC, update the firmware and you are set to go.<br /><br />The Gizmo is specifically designed for outdoor use and is Rigid in design as well as weather resistant. The enclosure is watertight which means that if you leave it in the rain it will be OK, if you drop it into the Bath Tub for a short period of time then it SHOULD be OK but if you go diving with it then most probably it will malfunction and eventually brake. The buttons are well spaced for cold weather environments where you would need gloves to make anything work. The LCD is back-lit for night use. The device has an Internal RF Receiver and can be even operated remotely.<br /><br />The device operates on a 9v battery so you can replace it and not worry about charging the device in the middle of a forest or a remote area.<br /><br /><strong>Main Features</strong><br /><br />-2 Camera outputs with Shutter &amp; Focus control<br />-3 Flash outputs<br />-2 Audio Inputs<br />-1 Specific Light input<br />-2 General Purpose Inputs<br />-128x64 Graphical Display<br />-3 Operational buttons<br />-Replaceable 9v battery compartment<br />-Watertight Design<br />-Rigid Enclosure for outdoor use<br />-Internal memory for setting storage<br />-USB Input for Firmware Updates &amp; PC Operation<br />-Internal RF Receiver (for the KeyFob Remote)<br />-USB Cable is included<br /><br /><strong>Additional Information</strong><br /><br />You can find more information about this Gizmo in our Projects and Blog sections of the website as well as the Forums, where we have descriptions and the workflow we went through for finishing this device.</p>\n<p>There are also many accessories available for this Gizmo. To find out what they are as well as what their cost is, please visit our website.</p>\n<div class="product-specs">\n<p>This Gizmo was created based on a wish that a member on our community made. The idea already existed for a device that could trigger a High Resolution Camera based on settings or sensors. With this Gizmo you can pretty much do everything you ever wanted with a Camera or multiple cameras, Flash units and sensors. Set up your scene as you want it, adjust the settings and sensors you need and simply wait for the device to do the rest. There are endless applications for this device and the only limit is your imagination. Use it for taking photos of Lightning as it strikes based on the sound or on the actual light emitted. Take photos of animals as they walk by without even touching the device. Laser Trigger or motion trigger the camera or even leave it for a long period of time and take pictures of a flower as it opens at sunrise and closes at sunset with intervals of your choosing. We have growing collection of sensors for this unit and always glad to make even more based on member requests. Since the software and hardware of this Gizmo (as any Gizmo we make) is Open Source, you can simply tell us a new feature or menu that you need and we shall add it for you. Plug it with a USB cable to your PC, update the firmware and you are set to go.</p>\n<br />\n<p>The Gizmo is specifically designed for outdoor use and is Rigid in design as well as weather resistant. The enclosure is watertight which means that if you leave it in the rain it will be OK, if you drop it into the Bath Tub for a short period of time then it SHOULD be OK but if you go diving with it then most probably it will malfunction and eventually brake. The buttons are well spaced for cold weather environments where you would need gloves to make anything work. The LCD is back-lit for night use. The device has an Internal RF Receiver and can be even operated remotely.</p>\n<br />\n<p>The device operates on a 9v battery so you can replace it and not worry about charging the device in the middle of a forest or a remote area.<strong></strong></p>\n<br />\n<h4>Main Features</h4>\n<br />\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">-2 Camera outputs with Shutter &amp; Focus control <br />-3 Flash outputs <br />-2 Audio Inputs <br />-1 Specific Light input <br />-2 General Purpose Inputs <br />-128x64 Graphical Display <br />-3 Operational buttons <br />-Replaceable 9v battery compartment <br />-Watertight Design <br />-Rigid Enclosure for outdoor use <br />-Internal memory for setting storage <br />-USB Input for Firmware Updates &amp; PC Operation <br />-Internal RF Receiver (for the KeyFob Remote) <br />-USB Cable is included</p>\n<br />\n<h3>Additional Information</h3>\n<p><br />You can find more information about this Gizmo in our Projects and Blog sections of the website as well as the Forums at <strong><a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.com">our website</a></strong>, where we have descriptions and the workflow we went through for finishing this device.</p>\n</div>', 1, '2011-04-26', 92, 15, ',distributor,funding,promotion', '<p>The product is shipped by EMS data post. It is ensured and arrives in approximately 10 - 15 working days.</p>', 1, 0),
