(346, 153, 'giZZle Beginner Kit', 115.00, 36.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<div class="product-specs">\n<p>The <a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.net/site/en/projects.html?section=projects&amp;workspace=35&amp;task=display_details&amp;id=35&amp;1c233f3dfd42791f9735ebeb62f2c56e=1" target="_blank">giZZle project</a> initially started as an idea when Gizmo For You just begun standing on its own two feet. After many hours of brain storming and R&amp;D we came up with a simple way of creating electronic circuits which doesn''t require any soldering whatsoever and still allows any user to generate a design as complex as he/she likes.</p>\n<p>giZZle is a way of assembling schematic designs in a form of puzzle pieces with internally installed components. Each piece can have a component such as a resistor, capacitor or even a motor or a speaker. Each piece can have up to 12 connections which can interact individually with each piece and formulate a circuit.</p>\n<p>The heart of the giZZle design is a mechanism which contains a set of springs and brass balls which when touch each other, spring back without loosing a connection. To make sure that there is no loss in a connection we made the internal board touch each brass ball from the top as well as from the bottom. What makes the design affordable is it''s simple and modular construction. Each piece is assembled from 3 different PCB''s, allowing us to place a component internally without having anything sticking out of the part it self and seal it all with a top cap which is made of the same material. All tracks and connections are Gold Plated, meaning that there is no corrosion or harmful chemicals even after a long usage period. To top it all off all boards are ROH compliant and environment friendly.</p>\n<p>The Beginner kit was especially assembled with all necessary parts to begin working with it, without additional components. The kit contains 16 giZZle pieces including a battery housing for 4 AA batteries as well as a connector for a 9v battery so that you can choose which one to use in your next project. Even the Box for the kit was especially designed to house it''s components and is hand crafted one by one by our hard working team members.</p>\n<h4>What''s inside the box</h4>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">- 1 x 453 oHm Resistor Piece<br />- 1 x 10k Variable Resistor Piece<br />- 1 x PNP Transistor Piece<br />- 1 x NPN Transistor Piece<br />- 1 x Diode Piece<br />- 1 x Push Button Piece <br />- 1 x Photo Resistor Piece<br />- 1 x Vibrator Motor Piece<br />- 1 x 0.3W Loud Speaker Piece<br />- 1 x 3mm Green LED with an internal resistor Piece <br />- 3 x All Side Corner Piece<br />- 2 x Straight Connection Piece <br />- 1 x Power Supply connector Piece<br />- 1 x 4 Cell AA Battery Housing <br />- 1 x 9v Battery Connector <br />- Beginner Kit User Guide</p>\n<h4>Community</h4>\n<p>Although you will find a detailed explanation of all components in the kit in the User Guide, we have a wonderful community where we update new ideas as well as new giZZle parts all the time. If you get bored with what you read in the Guide then don''t forget to check out the <a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.net/site/gizmocommunity/groups/viewgroup/12-giZZle.html" target="_blank">giZZle Community Group</a> as well as our Forum where everyone can share new ideas or suggestions.</p>\n<h3>Additional Information</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.net/site/en/gizmocommunity/groups/viewgroup/12-giZZle.html" target="_blank"><strong>giZZle Community Group</strong></a> - This is the official community Group for the Gizmo <br /><a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.net/forum/viewforum.php?f=85" target="_blank"><strong>giZZle Forum</strong></a> - This is the official forum thread for the Gizmo</p>\n<p>You can find more information about this Gizmo in our <a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.net/site/en/projects.html" target="_blank"><strong>Projects</strong></a> and <a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.net/site/en/blogs.html" target="_blank"><strong>Blog</strong></a> sections of the website as well as the <a href="http://www.gizmoforyou.net/forum/" target="_blank"><strong>Forums</strong></a>, where we have descriptions and the workflow we went through for finishing this device.</p>\n</div>', 1, '2011-06-06', 92, 5, ',distributor,funding,,', '<p>The product is shipped by EMS data post. It is ensured and arrives in approximately 10 - 15 working days.</p>', 1, 1),
