(195, 133, 'wooden iPhone case PC002', 39.00, 5.00, '', 'iphone,wooden,apple,case,design', 5, 'Wooden iPhone case for 4G<br /><br />We have a different selection of wood: <br />Oak and Ash <br /><br />Wood is the best material. It''s second only to leather for how nice it feels in the hand&mdash;and even that''s debatable. It is theoretically sustainable, assuaging the tortured consumer soul with eco-positive lubrication. And it''s just pretty. <br />Weight 50g <br />Material : Wood', 1, '2011-05-01', 121, 15, ',,,,', '<div align="left">Ready to dispatch in: 3-5 working days after receipt of payment</div>', 1, 0),
(167, 144, 'Wall Clock was an Apple Power Mac G4 Front Panel', 49.00, 15.00, '', 'apple clock,apple G4 clock,computer clock,recycled,wall clock', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">This <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wall Clock is a former Apple Power Macintosh G4</strong></span> desktop computer front control panel.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This stunning wall clock has it''s original dark and light gray translucent finish with black metal hour and minute hands with "Macintosh apple-red" second hand</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The clock''s hands appear through the Apple Computer''s former front speaker.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The top and bottom of the panel are accented by the former Apple G4''s clear acrylic carry handles.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Artist signed and numbered "Certificate of Authenticity."</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Approximately 8" wide by 16" tall.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A "home decor" or office conversation piece.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">"These are great! Love em!" -- Lizz B., TEcoArt customer </span></p>', 1, '2011-05-19', 114, 15, ',,,,', '<p><span style="font-size: small;">We ship <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">USPS Priority Mail with Tracking Number</span></strong>. We ship first thing in the morning day after order.&nbsp; We ship the same way for International Orders unless First Class Mail is requested.&nbsp; First Class Mail does not have Tracking Number.</span></p>', 1, 0),
(577, 21, 'DJ Girl Glass Metal Frame Pendant Necklace', 15.00, 2.50, '', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">A reversible frame pendant necklace showcasing two versions of the DJ Girl. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This delicate reversible glass pendant displays two small 1x2" inch original blueorder photographs (one on each side); The DJ Girl is shown in black and white, while on the other side is displayed in a rose/purple shade. The glass pendant has been closed and cannot reopen. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A silver ball chain of approximately 24" inches in length is included. You can also cut the chain to size. Better yet, you can use your favorite chain to hang this piece.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The metal has a silver look, but is not silver. This pendant cannot withstand water.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Please contact me for any questions.</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-24', 171, 3, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(578, 23, 'Polaroid Swinger and Land Camera Glass Metal Frame', 13.00, 2.50, '', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">A reversible frame pendant necklace showcasing two classic Polaroid cameras, Land and Swinger</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This delicate reversible glass pendant displays two small 1x1" inch original blueorder photographs (one on each side); Yellow Polaroid and a Swinger. The glass pendant has been closed and cannot reopen. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A silver ball chain of approximately 24" inches in length is included. You can also cut the chain to size. Better yet, you can use your favorite chain to hang this piece.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The metal has a silver look, but is not silver. This pendant cannot withstand water.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Please contact me for any questions.</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-24', 171, 3, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(576, 23, 'Nintendo Controller Mix - Coaster Table Art', 29.00, 6.00, '', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">Original blueorder photography and art enclosed in my own handmade frame for table top/coaster or wall display. Reverse side will be either black or silver; based on existing supplies.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This photo shown is a stacked photo modification of my early model Nintendo game system controller. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">*Sawtooth hanger attached for easy wall display.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">*Size is 8"x10".</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Any photo seen in another listing in my store can be purchased alone or can be interchanged and placed in a clock or giant coaster. Please email me with any questions.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The construction of this piece involves a photograph, covered and locked with previously prepared plastic and anti-skid coated nuts.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">For cleaning: Avoid using abrasive or highly alkaline cleaners.</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-24', 171, 11, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(171, 166, 'Apple iPod Hard Drive Clock on a Circuit Board', 35.00, 8.00, '', 'apple clock,circuit board clocl,ipod clock,desk clock,unique gift', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">A must have for the Apple geek!</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The clock is created from an interesting circuit board that used to control a computer hard drive!</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The clock face is an actual Apple iPod disk drive including the mirror-faced disk platter.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Approximately 3.5" wide by 5.5" tall.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">"This is a great way to recycle older technology into once again, useful items." -- comment from Technology Blog on tEcoArt</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">These are wonderful conversation pieces and unique gifts for family, friends and co-workers. </span><br /><br />Artist signed and numbered "Certificate of Authenticity."</p>', 1, '2011-04-29', 114, 5, ',,,,', '<p><span style="font-size: small;">We ship <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">USPS Priority Mail with Tracking Number</span></strong>. We ship first thing in the morning day after order.&nbsp; We ship the same way for International Orders unless First Class Mail is requested.&nbsp; First Class Mail does not have Tracking Number.</span></p>', 1, 0),
(172, 141, 'iClock is a former Apple iBook Blueberry Clamshell', 68.00, 15.00, '', 'apple clock,iclock,apple wall clock,pendulum clock,clock', 1, '<p><strong><span style="font-size: small;">Clock dial is a former Apple iBook G3 Clamshell laptop computer keyboard section.</span></strong><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This stunning pendulum wall clock has its original aqua blue, white and transparent finish with black metal hour and minute hands and an "apple red" second hand.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The clock top has been accented with the iBook Clamshell''s former mouse as the pendulum weight, awesome highlight!</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Artist signed and numbered "Certificate of Authenticity."</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Approximately 13" wide by 16" tall including pendulum and mouse.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A "home decor" or office conversation piece.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">"This is a great way to recycle older technology into once again, useful items." -- comment from Technology Blog on TEcoArt. </span></p>', 1, '2011-04-29', 114, 5, ',,,,', '<p><span style="font-size: small;">We ship <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">USPS Priority Mail with Tracking Number</span></strong>. We ship first thing in the morning day after order.&nbsp; We ship the same way for International Orders unless First Class Mail is requested.&nbsp; First Class Mail does not have Tracking Number.</span></p>', 1, 1),
(173, 199, 'Rare 1980s Control Data Hard Drive now a Hard Driv', 199.00, 13.00, '', '1980s,hard drive clock,rare hard drive,desk clock,unique gift', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">A very rare and original middle 1980s Control Data Corporation (CDC) 8" hard drive recycled as a clock.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Of the thousands of hard drives we have reclaimed and recycled, this is the only one of this type and vintage that we have ever seen.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">These drives were used in the earliest "mini and micro" computers of the day. The disk platter is a very early 5.25" platter that could hold only 3.5 megabytes of data. The drive had 3 disk platters combined to hold 10 megabytes of data.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">We have seen vintage ads showing this type of drive selling for $3,695 in the day! That''s $369 per megabyte. Compare that to today''s prices of about $.08 per megabyte (1 terabyte drive=1000 megabytes for about $80.) One of the attached pictures shows this drive compared to a current desktop computer''s 3.5" drive.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Clock dial is the actual ferrite coated disk platter from this vintage hard drive. Age has not affected the disk platter in any way, it is pristine and quite stunning.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Black metal hour and minute clock hands tell the time, the second hand is one of our interesting "zigzag" designs.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Accenting the upper left corner of the hard drive is the actual "disk platter clamp" that was used to hold the platters in place on the spindle shaft.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The "read-write head" is still attached with all of its workings.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The base was a hard drive''s former cover left in its original condition (with minor scratches.)</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Accenting the base is the disk spindle motor cover with original markings as well as the ribbon cable that was connected to its controller circuit board.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Artist signed and numbered "Certificate of Authenticity."</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Approx. 5.5" wide by 8" tall.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">"This clock was fashioned from a mid-1980s PC''s hard drive, already very difficult to find. Unfortunately most of them are already in landfills...we were too late!" -- R. Connolly, TEcoArt</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Get one for the serious collector or become one with this rare clock.</span></p>', 1, '2011-05-16', 114, 17, ',,,,', '<p><span style="font-size: small;">We ship <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">USPS Priority Mail with Tracking Number</span></strong>. We ship first thing in the morning day after order.&nbsp; We ship the same way for International Orders unless First Class Mail is requested.&nbsp; First Class Mail does not have Tracking Number.</span></p>', 1, 0),
