(192, 68, 'Blue Wiimote Parody Soap Pepsi-type Scent', 11.00, 4.00, '', 'soap,geek,Nintendo,Wii ,Wiimote', 5, '<p><strong>Another DigitalSoaps original! This white Wiimote replica soap contains the detail of the real thing. It even includes most of a trigger button.&nbsp;</strong><br /><br />Perhaps best of all, it is scented with Pepsi-type fragrance oil.<br /><br />Weighs 4.5 ounces.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>One word of caution. There is no wrist strap, so use at your own risk!&nbsp;</strong><br /><br />This product is vegan. Shipped worldwide by Priority Mail.&nbsp;<br /><br />Soap ingredients for you scientists out there:<br /><br />&middot; Coconut Oil<br />&middot; Palm Oil<br />&middot; Safflower Oil<br />&middot; Glycerin (kosher, of vegetable origin)<br />&middot; Purified Water<br />&middot; Sodium Hydroxide (saponifying agent)<br />&middot; Sorbitol (moisturizer)<br />&middot; Sorbitan Oleate (emulsifier)<br />&middot; Soy Bean Protein (conditioner)<br />&middot; Fragrance and color<br /><br />About DigitalSoaps and founder Chrystal Doucette:<br /><br />I invented soap shaped like video game controllers and other electronics on a whim. My soap is the first to communicate with subcultures of gamers and geeks. I haven''t seen anything like it and I haven''t seen gamers this excited about soap. Every single game controller design you see in my shop was the first in existence.&nbsp;<br /><br />My first video game-themed soap, a PlayStation 2 replica controller, received so much attention, I decided to start making more video game controller replicas. Due to the overwhelming success of this concept, I was able to leave the 24-7 world of news reporting.<br /><br />When you buy a soap from me, you are supporting a small business and you are supporting the original artist of these types of soaps.&nbsp;<br /><br />Each product is made in my home. I remain committed to using only high quality, vegan ingredients in my soap.<br /><br />You can find my soaps covered at Computer idee (Netherlands), GamePro, GamesMaster (Germany), GEE Magazine (Germany), Forbes, Liberating Style, Komo 4 News (Seattle) Micro Hebdo (France), Thrillist (Boston and Seattle), Wired UK, and WonkaVision. GamePro gave my soap the Editors'' Choice Award!&nbsp;<br /><br />I HAS A SOCIAL NETWORK:<br />http://twitter.com/DigitalSoaps<br />www.facebook.com/pages/DigitalSoaps/205525062068</p>', 1, '2011-04-30', 119, 15, ',,funding,promotion,', '<p>Shipping generally takes 2-3 days from your date of purchase, except during peak holiday times. Your order will be shipped by First Class mail for items under 13 ounces, and by Priority Mail for items weighing more than 13 ounces. Purchases that weigh a lot may be shipped by Parcel Post.&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0);
