(310, 71, 'SOAP SNES Parody by DigitalSoaps- Green Apple Cand', 10.00, 4.00, '', 'SNES,geeks,soap,nintendo,gamers', 10, '<p>This is another DigitalSoaps original invention.&nbsp;<br /><br />I made a SNES controller replica soap, with raised massaging buttons.&nbsp;<br /><br />Weighs 4.5 ounces and scented with "green apple candy" fragrance oil.&nbsp;<br /><br />All my soaps are vegan.<br /><br />You can build a custom bar of soap at www.digitalsoaps.net!<br /><br />Soap Ingredients:<br /><br />&middot; Coconut Oil<br />&middot; Palm Oil<br />&middot; Castor Oil<br />&middot; Safflower Oil<br />&middot; Glycerin (kosher, of vegetable origin)<br />&middot; Purified Water<br />&middot; Sodium Hydroxide (saponifying agent)<br />&middot; Sorbitol (moisturizer)<br />&middot; Sorbitan Oleate (emulsifier)<br />&middot; Soy Bean Protein (conditioner)<br />&middot; Titanium Dioxide (mineral whitener used in opaque soaps)<br />&middot; Fragrance and color<br /><br />About DigitalSoaps and founder Chrystal Doucette:<br /><br />I invented soap shaped like video game controllers and other electronics on a whim. My soap is the first to communicate with subcultures of gamers and geeks. I haven''t seen anything like it and I haven''t seen gamers this excited about soap. Every single game controller design you see in my shop was the first in existence.&nbsp;<br /><br />My first video game-themed soap, a PlayStation 2 replica controller, received so much attention, I decided to start making more video game controller replicas. Due to the overwhelming success of this concept, I was able to leave the 24-7 world of news reporting.<br /><br />When you buy a soap from me, you are supporting a small business and you are supporting the original artist of these types of soaps.&nbsp;<br /><br />Each product is made in my home. I remain committed to using only high quality, vegan ingredients in my soap.<br /><br />You can find my soaps covered at Computer idee (Netherlands), GamePro, GamesMaster (Germany), GEE Magazine (Germany), Forbes, Liberating Style, Komo 4 News (Seattle) Micro Hebdo (France), Thrillist (Boston and Seattle), Wired UK, and WonkaVision. GamePro gave my soap the Editors'' Choice Award!&nbsp;<br /><br />I HAS A SOCIAL NETWORK:<br />http://twitter.com/DigitalSoaps<br />www.facebook.com/pages/DigitalSoaps/205525062068<br /><br />DigitalSoaps: Original inventor of geek and gamer soap.</p>', 1, '2011-05-24', 119, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 1),
(311, 106, 'SOAP Companion Cube- Mountain Dew-type Scented by ', 23.00, 5.00, '', 'Soap,Portal,Companion Cube,gamer,gifts', 3, '<p><strong>"The Enrichment Center reminds you that the Weighted Companion Cube will never threaten to stab you and, in fact, cannot speak. In the event that the Weighted Companion Cube does speak, the Enrichment Center urges you to disregard its advice."</strong><br /><br />Imagine, if you will, a companion cube so sweet it cleans you in the shower. A silent companion cube, gentle and square.&nbsp;<br /><br />Behold! The companion cube soap. This parody is more than 9 ounces in size and is Green Apple Candy scented. There''s a Mountain Dew-type scented one in the shop too :)&nbsp;<br /><br />This one takes a bit of time to create for you. It may take up to four days to ship.&nbsp;<br /><br />There will be unavoidable flaws in this soap, proof of its handmade nature. I make each one carefully.&nbsp;<br /><br />Made by the original inventor of geek, gamer and gadget soap, DigitalSoaps.&nbsp;<br /><br />You can find my soaps covered in Computer idee (Netherlands), GamePro, GamesMaster (German), GEE Magazine (German), Forbes.com, Micro Hebdo (French), New York Daily News, Wired UK and WonkaVision. My soap was also featured on Komo 4 News, Thrillist, and HGTV!<br /><br /><br />Shrink wrapped for gift giving.&nbsp;<br /><br />Ingredients<br />&middot; Coconut Oil<br />&middot; Palm Oil<br />&middot; Safflower Oil<br />&middot; Glycerin (kosher, of vegetable origin)<br />&middot; Purified Water<br />&middot; Sodium Hydroxide (saponifying agent)<br />&middot; Sorbitol (moisturizer)<br />&middot; Sorbitan Oleate (emulsifier)<br />&middot; Soy Bean Protein (conditioner)<br />&middot; Titanium Dioxide (mineral whitener used in opaque soaps)<br />&middot; Fragrance and color<br /><br />About DigitalSoaps and founder Chrystal Doucette:<br />I invented soap shaped like video game controllers and other electronics on a whim. My soap is the first to communicate with subcultures of gamers and geeks. I haven''t seen anything like it and I haven''t seen gamers this excited about soap.<br /><br />When I was younger, my dad took me to Computer City. A<br />trip highlight included the chocolate 5.25-inch floppy disks the store sold. With a desire to relive my past, I checked online to see if anyone still sold the chocolate disks. I didn''t find any. But during my research, I found plenty of chocolate molds shaped like electronics. This discovery sparked the idea of making soap. I was already a fan of handmade soap, so the two ideas merged well.<br /><br />My first video game-themed soap, a PlayStation 2 replica controller, received so much attention, I decided to start making more video game controller replicas. I was able to leave the 24-7 world of news reporting for a much more zen existence. When you buy a soap from me, you are supporting a small business and you are supporting the original artist of these types of soaps.&nbsp;<br /><br />Each product is made in my home. I remain committed to using only high quality, vegan ingredients in my soap.</p>', 1, '2011-05-24', 119, 11, ',,,,', '', 1, 1),
