(349, 49, '8-bit Legacy NES Advantage Joystick Desktop Lamp', 21.00, 6.00, '', 'Nintendo,NES,Lamp,Desktop,Smooth Criminal', 1, '<p>**PREPARE FOR DIRECT TRANSMISSION FROM RETRO-HQ**<br />&lt;TRANSMISSION PASSCODE: ILLUMINATIONMATRIX&gt;<br />&lt;&lt;DATA TRACKS OF: GAMESMYTHE&gt;&gt;<br /><br />We thought we were doing the right thing. The popularity of the GameTime! Clocks were overwhelming. There wasn''t a single person who thought that moving forward with the Retrofication Experiments was a bad idea.<br /><br />Little did we know....<br /><br />It was simple. Modify a Retro to provide the lighting gamers of past, present and future would need for the late nights needed to progress through their respective digital realms.<br /><br />We cleansed the Retro and prepped it for the upgrades. The procedure went off without a hitch, there wasn''t any hint of what was to come. We topped it off with a nice Light Neutralization guard that clipped onto the accompanying 40watt illumination bulb.<br /><br />Upon it''s reactivation, it presented with no abnormal behavior. The Prototype was sitting on the desk of our main system and aiding in the creation of others. Perhaps there was an ulterior motive here....maybe a Retro army to take over? Quite possible. It converted others of it''s ilk. It very well may be a side effect from the Retrofication Mods, or the Retro could''ve been abnormal from the start.<br /><br />If that''s the case, does that mean I zombiefied them via retrofication? Or just empower them with the gear they needed?<br /><br />I...I barricaded myself in the Dungeon''s Communications area. If they learned how to modify each other even further, I''m not going to last long. No one will. I...I think I just heard something...I just hope my cordless Dremel is enough to hold them at bay. I can''t remember the last time I put the power pack on the charg*****<br /><br />***TRANSMISSION INTURRUPTED***<br /><br /><br />&lt;&lt;Renegade Retro Scan Results&gt;&gt;<br /><br />Subject: Protoform X-42 Alpha<br /><br />Projected Upgrade Status: Joystick -&gt; Desklamp<br /><br />Project Status: Successful Prototyping<br /><br />Equipment Status:<br /><br />Subject is now equipped with a Push Style Activation Switch that is powered by a standard outlet.&nbsp;<br /><br />The Light Core works best with the currently equipped 40 watt Illumination Bulb, but we don''t know the extent of what size wattage it can utilize due to it''s rebellion before successful testing.<br /><br />The Shading Apparatus provides a shielding against the full force of the Illumination Bulb as it clips on securely to the Bulb itself.&nbsp;<br /><br />&lt;&lt;End of Equipment Scan Results&gt;&gt;</p>', 1, '2011-06-07', 142, 17, ',distributor,,promotion,', '<p>Each item is shipped via USPS, the day after the construction is completed and the payment has cleared. Construction can take Two to Three weeks depending on what parts and gear we have in stock. Insurance is the responsibility of the customer, and please let us know of any special requests such as gift wrapping, or shipping to another address.</p>', 1, 0),
(348, 106, 'GameTime NES Advantage Clock', 20.00, 6.00, '', 'NES,CLOCK,GAME,Nintendo,Retro', 1, '<p>With this unique clock, you can look up and see it''s time to place that call to your boss and tell him that you''re "sick".<br /><br /><br /><br />Each clock is painstakingly RETROfitted in our Dungeon by our GameSmyth from a vintage Nintendo Advantage Joystick. It comes with the single AA battery that guarantees accurate time for each and every gaming session to come!<br /><br />This looks great sitting on a desk or mounted on the wall! Don''t miss out on having a piece of your childhood hanging on your wall to remind you of those weekends spent eating cereal and watching Saturday morning cartoons...and as soon as those were over, the power button was hit, and it was Game On!<br /><br />Due to the nature of RETROfitting, the item will have minor scuffs and marks. We use only the best condition we can find, and rest assured if we wouldn''t sport it, we won''t sell it!&nbsp;<br /><br />Each piece is constructed to order, so it can take anywhere from one to three weeks to complete if supplies are low, we are backed up or there is a customization request on the item.</p>', 1, '2011-06-07', 142, 17, ',distributor,,promotion,', '<p>Each item is shipped via USPS, the day after the construction is completed and the payment has cleared. Construction can take Two to Three weeks depending on what parts and gear we have in stock. Insurance is the responsibility of the customer, and please let us know of any special requests such as gift wrapping, or shipping to another address.</p>', 1, 1),
(350, 48, 'Gygaxs Legacy - 20 Sided Dice Keychain Chomp', 2.00, 1.39, '', 'D20,Gygax,Dungeons,Dragons,D&D', 5, '<p>We''re not really into the realm of anything other than Retro Gaming...or so we thought. You can''t get much more Retro than this!&nbsp;<br /><br />Coming from the days of when table top gaming was at it''s peak we have a selection of 20 Sided Dice that has been Keychain Chomped.<br /><br />They come in a variety of colors, and if you don''t see one, you can just request it, and we''ll get back to you quick and let you know if we have it or can get it.<br /><br />Simple. Effective. Plus it adds +22 to your Charisma.</p>', 1, '2011-06-07', 142, 17, ',distributor,,promotion,', '<p>Each item is shipped via USPS, the day after the construction is completed and the payment has cleared. Construction can take Two to Three weeks depending on what parts and gear we have in stock. Insurance is the responsibility of the customer, and please let us know of any special requests such as gift wrapping, or shipping to another address.</p>', 1, 0),
(351, 316, '8-bit Legacy NES Zapper Desktop Lamp', 28.00, 9.00, '', 'NES,Zapper,Nintendo,Lamp,Retro', 4, '<p>lose your eyes and relax. Remember. It''s your birthday or Christmas. You open up your Nintendo Control Deck. The Action set! A game?! Score! What?&nbsp;<br /><br />That''s right. Two or even THREE games! On one cartridge! That was most of our experience! The first Zapper experience we ever had was Duck hunt!&nbsp;<br /><br />Here is our tribute to that! An upturned NES Zapper is attached solidly to it''s Duck Hunt Cartridge Base! What better way to pay homage to our Zapper Memories and dreams of shooting that damn laughing dog?!&nbsp;<br /><br />This lamp is activated by a push switch at the base of the light socket, and the power plug comes out of the handle of the gun like the original cable!&nbsp;<br /><br />The lampshade attaches to the bulb itself in case you want to make small adjustments!<br /><br />Now! Here''s the fun:&nbsp;<br />Gun Color can be specified. Orange or Grey. If it''s not specified, then it is picked at random.&nbsp;<br /><br />Due to the nature of the base, (It being an actual Nintendo Game!), it can be exchanged from the standard Duck Hunt game, to another Zapper Game, for an additional $5.00. This adds an additional week, maybe less, to procure the game if it is not in our stock. If the game is more expensive than the standard, then that will increase the price. We''ll contact you ahead of time to secure your thumbs up!<br /><br />We here at Recycled Retro are constantly innovating and tampering with Retros! We hope you enjoy our latest invention and have fun in World 2-3!<br /><br />Below is a list of Zapper based games.<br /><br />* The Adventures of Bayou Billy (gun optional)<br />* Barker Bill''s Trick Shooting<br />* Duck Hunt<br />* Freedom Force<br />* Gotcha! The Sport!<br />* Gumshoe<br />* Hogan''s Alley<br />* Laser Invasion<br />* The Lone Ranger (gun optional)<br />* Mechanized Attack<br />* Operation Wolf (gun optional)<br />* Shooting Range (requires gun and controller)<br />* To The Earth<br />* Track &amp; Field II (Gun compatible)<br />* Wild Gunman</p>', 1, '2011-06-07', 142, 17, ',distributor,,promotion,', '<p>Each item is shipped via USPS, the day after the construction is completed and the payment has cleared. Construction can take Two to Three weeks depending on what parts and gear we have in stock. Insurance is the responsibility of the customer, and please let us know of any special requests such as gift wrapping, or shipping to another address.</p>', 1, 1),
(352, 46, 'NES Keychain-Chomp', 2.00, 1.39, '', 'NES,Nintendo,Keychain,Retro,Recycled', 5, '<p>With this simple, yet stylish, piece every gamer will identify you as one of their own.&nbsp;<br /><br />Presenting the NES Style Keychain-Chomp! Now, with an improved Key Interlock System!<br /><br />Each one is removed from a controller, or accessory and is put through our thorough process that involves a mad scientists lab, two bolts in it''s neck, and a lightning storm.&nbsp;<br /><br />In the end we need to de-animate it so we can put a keyring on it, but it''s worth it...and we do it...all for you.</p>', 1, '2011-06-07', 142, 17, ',distributor,,promotion,', '<p>Each item is shipped via USPS, the day after the construction is completed and the payment has cleared. Construction can take Two to Three weeks depending on what parts and gear we have in stock. Insurance is the responsibility of the customer, and please let us know of any special requests such as gift wrapping, or shipping to another address.</p>', 1, 0),
