(483, 159, 'The Contega for iPad2', 89.99, 10.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">In days of old it was said that the muses would visit creativity and inspiration upon a person, and that person was said to have a genius.&nbsp;While we''d love to credit our latest ingenuity to Greece, the birthplace of western civilization, our newest creation is truly a credit to our Norske heritage, the Vikings!&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Framed in rugged but light weight Baltic Birch that is lacquer finished and bound in subtle, yet durable bonded Italian leather, this case adds a whole new versatility to your iPad2.&nbsp;Like having Adrian Peterson in your backfield, our gorgeous leather case plays multiple roles as a cover, a stand, a sound amplifier and concealment to protect against theft.&nbsp;And, in the case of an incidental fumble, this rugged case adds extra protection that other cases simply don''t offer.&nbsp;&nbsp;Presenting our newest addition to the PQ bookshelf.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">The Contega for iPad2.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>NOTE -- Please indicate which color you would like -- Classic Red, Camden Blue, or Field Green </strong></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: small;">Features:</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Italian bonded leather cover</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">-&nbsp;Multiple standing positions&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">-&nbsp;Hidden pocket included!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Rugged design to protect your iPad2</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- 3 internal COLOR options</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Access to all ports</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Very secure bumper/wood system to hold your iPad2</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Lacquer finished Baltic birch wood</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Camera access</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Magnetic on/off feature</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Classic journal/moleskin elastic closure</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><br /></span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 161, 8, ',,,,', '<p>Priority Mail <em class="ProductPrice">$10.00</em></p>\n<p><em class="ProductPrice">Express Mail PLEASE NOTE:Sent at expected ship time listed on website <em class="ProductPrice">$35.00</em><br /></em></p>', 1, 1),
(484, 45, 'The Octavo for iPad2', 59.99, 10.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">What&rsquo;s in a name? A rose by any other would smell as sweet.&nbsp; But that particular &ldquo;rose&rdquo; smells terribly clich&eacute; and clich&eacute; was the last thing on our minds when the tiny seeds of our new case company were beginning to bud.&nbsp;</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> Yet how does one convey in a word the allure of 8 Baltic birch veneers lacquered to manifest an extraordinary depth of beauty and routered to precisely encase an iPad 2?&nbsp; Or explain in a single name the resplendent feel of Italian bonded leather binding, hand sculpted with specific detail? Well, frankly you don&rsquo;t and that is why a picture is worth a thousand words and a lot less headache to our web designer.&nbsp; However, here is our newest rose&hellip;</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;"> The Octavo for iPad2. </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>NOTE: Please pick an inside color Classic Red, Camden Blue and Field Green.</strong><br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: small;">Features:</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- The slimmest design ever produced by Pad&amp;Quill.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- <span style="font-weight: bold;">NEW</span> 3 beautiful cloth colors - Classic Red, Camden Blue and Field Green.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- <span style="font-weight: bold;">NEW</span> optional interior pocket available in all colors.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Holds the iPad 2 very securely with proprietary bumper materials.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Covered in Italian bonded leather.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- The &lsquo;bookmark&rsquo; for easier device removal</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Patented sound channel</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Wrap around spine for multiple viewing configurations</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Hand made in the Twin Cities, USA</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">- Includes the Magnetic on/off feature</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 161, 8, ',,,,', '<p>Priority Mail <em class="ProductPrice">$10.00</em></p>\n<p><em class="ProductPrice">Express Mail PLEASE NOTE:Sent at expected ship time listed on website <em class="ProductPrice">$35.00</em></em></p>', 1, 0),
(485, 47, 'The Cartella for MacBook Air - 11 inch', 79.99, 10.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<h2><span style="font-size: small;">Our Sputnik Moment</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">They said is couldn''t be done and yet, Pad&amp;Quill is proud to present The Cartella. The one and only bookbindery case for the MacBook Air.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">The Cartella rhymes with bella which is exactly what you will think of our Italian leather bound case for the Macbook air. Designed with the same Baltic Birch frame as our other cases, this one pays tribute to the innovation that brought sleek design and functionality to the laptop market. For the device which redefined ordinary we present an extraordinary case.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Securing the MacBook Air within 1/20,000 of an inch this case offers the protection, functionality and luxury that you have come to expect from Pad&amp;Quill. Our proprietary bumper material keeps the laptop in place. Access to all major ports is available and when our unique portfolio book is folded back it provides a perfect laptop stand. A new large pocket space is now included&nbsp;for those documents and notes you need on the go.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Please refer to FAQ page for care of your bindery carry case.</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 161, 8, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(486, 47, 'The Cartella for MacBook Air - 13 inch', 89.99, 10.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<h2><span style="font-size: small;">Our Sputnik Moment</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">They said is couldn''t be done and yet, Pad&amp;Quill is proud to present The Cartella. The one and only bookbindery case for the MacBook Air.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">The Cartella rhymes with bella which is exactly what you will think of our Italian leather bound case for the Macbook air. Designed with the same Baltic Birch frame as our other cases, this one pays tribute to the innovation that brought sleek design and functionality to the laptop market. For the device which redefined ordinary we present an extraordinary case.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Securing the MacBook Air within 1/20,000 of an inch this case offers the protection, functionality and luxury that you have come to expect from Pad&amp;Quill. Our proprietary bumper material keeps the laptop in place. Access to all major ports is available and when our unique portfolio book is folded back it provides a perfect laptop stand. A new large pocket space is now included&nbsp;for those documents and notes you need on the go.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Please refer to FAQ page for care of your bindery carry case.</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 161, 8, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(487, 39, 'The Case for iPad - Volume 4', 59.99, 10.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<h2><span style="font-size: small;">Making the case for books!</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Most bookies love new editions. So does Pad&amp;Quill. Stay tuned for our announcement regarding our newest edition for the iPad 1.&nbsp;The Case, Volume 4! Same gorgeous bound Italian leather and rugged Baltic birch frame, but now with rounded corners and slimmer dimensions. &nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">The Case Vol. 4 allows you to hold your iPad like a favorite old book. However, this book has a wrap around cover that won''t break its spine when a flat surface is required. Vol. 4 can be propped up on non slick surfaces for viewing and includes our patent pending sound channel, moleskin style strap enclosure and classic red bookmark that allows for removal.&nbsp;When it comes to iPad accessories, we are making the case for books!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Please refer to FAQ page for care of your bindery carry case.</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 161, 8, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(488, 42, 'The Little Black Book for iPhone4 - Vol 3', 39.99, 10.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<h2><span style="font-size: small;">The Newest Little Black Book, Vol. 3</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">The new Little Black Book, Vol.3 is loaded with curves and sex appeal.&nbsp;But rather then hosting a sultry list of gold diggers, this gorgeous, new, Little Black Book is crafted to showcase your iPhone 4.&nbsp;Featuring 3 new colors with durable bookbindery cloth that match our Octavo for iPad2.&nbsp;Employing rugged Baltic Birch as our other cases, the classic bookmark for device removal and of course we bind it in subtle Italian bonded leather.&nbsp;This beauty is leaner, lighter and we rounded its edges to allow for an easier slide in and out of pockets.&nbsp; A gorgeous new addition to the Pad&amp;Quill bookshelf!</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Please refer to FAQ page for care of your bindery carry case.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: small;">Features:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Our smallest moleskin style case for the iPhone4 to date</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Italian bonded leather cover</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - 3 beautiful new interior colors (That match the Octavo!)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Tougher bookbindery cloth liner</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Subtle rounded corners</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Camera access </span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Classic bookmark</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - VERY snug fit with proprietary bumpers</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>NOTE: Please pick an inside color Classic Red, Camden Blue and Field Green.</strong></span><br /></span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 161, 8, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(489, 38, 'The Little Black Book for iPhone4 - Vol 1', 29.99, 10.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<h2><span style="font-size: small;">Celebrate with us!</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Our Little Black Books were featured by wired.com at the 2011 CES conference in Las Vegas!&nbsp;To celebrate we are dropping the price of Vol.1 for the iPhone4.&nbsp;Leave others intrigued and make a statement with the only little black book that&nbsp;carries your iPhone4.&nbsp; Covered in simulated leather the Little Black Book for iPhone 4 is the most beautiful and protective case on the market!</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Please refer to FAQ page for care of your bindery carry case.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>NOTE: Please pick an inside color Classic Red, Camden Blue and Field Green.</strong></span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 161, 8, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(490, 40, 'The Little Black Book for iPod Touch', 39.99, 10.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<h2><span style="font-size: small;">Available for iPod Touch - 2nd, 3rd, and 4th generation</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">There is something alluring about the little black book and we think you will be easily as intrigued by our Pad&amp;Quill take on this classic. Designed as a slim journal that slips comfortably into your purse, messenger bag or backpack, our Little Black Book also cradles your phone in a protective, hand- crafted wood frame. The comfortable feel of black leather binding, wrap around strap and classic red bookmark combine to dress your iPod in vintage style.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Please refer to FAQ page for care of your bindery carry case.</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 161, 8, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(491, 37, 'The Case for Kindle 3', 49.99, 10.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<h2><span style="font-size: small;">Making the case for books!</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">We are proud to announce the beautiful, handmade bookbindery case for the Kindle 3! Covered in Italian leather this case provides rugged protection, while creating the feel of holding a traditional book in your hand.&nbsp;Hand made in Minneapolis these cases are designed with precision cuts to fit your Kindle perfectly, allowing for easy access to the functions of your device. Then using traditional bookbindery techniques we cover the frame with a premium Italian leather cover and beautiful deep red interior paper.&nbsp;Our unique cranberry ''book mark'' allows for simple removal of the device and a classic ''moleskin'' strap helps keep the case closed for travel or going back on the bookshelf.&nbsp; We even included unique sound channels within our case to reflect the sounds back to the listener.&nbsp;Go ahead and get cozy with a great new read with our unique bookbindery case for the Kindle 3!</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Please refer to FAQ page for care of your bindery carry case.</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 161, 8, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(492, 41, 'The NookBook Color', 49.99, 10.00, '', ',,,,', 100, '<h2><span style="font-size: small;">Just look what we''ve cooked up in our innovation lab!</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">The NookBook for the Nook Color and Nook.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">We''ve crafted this case from a precision routered Baltic Birch frame that''s been hand sanded then coated in an environmentally friendly laquer.&nbsp;&nbsp;Next, each case is exquisitely bound in a subtle, Italian Bonded leather, and finished with our patented red book mark. So whether you''re enjoying a great read by the lake or perusing a textbook while riding the city bus, The Nook Book allows you to utilize your favorite e-reader without sacrificing the look and feel of a classic book.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Please refer to FAQ page for care of your bindery carry case.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: small;">Features:</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: small;">- Hand made here in Minneapolis</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Feels like a real book&hellip;because it is!</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Italian bonded leather cover</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Finished Baltic Birch wood frame</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Beautiful red interior paper</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Access to all functions</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Elastic strap closure</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;"> - Front cover folds back like a &lsquo;paperback&rsquo;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><br /></span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 161, 8, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(493, 42, 'MODULATRONICATRON 7000', 1000.00, 30.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A8Mv1XTtsnE ', ',,,,', 1, '<h1>It''s not too late to join the picnic synth revolution, with the MODULATRONICATRON 7000</h1>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Yes you heard right! Don''t be left in the dust this summer/fall/winter, sitting at home playing with something digital while all the cool kids in town are waxing glitchy and riding cubic waves of analog squarewave synthiness.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Features built in power supply, secured via the miracle of VELCRO, as well as a battery pack big enough to synth through even the most demanding camping/picnical situations. Onboard speaker, audio output jack, and various knobs and switches conspire to broadcast the impression that this picnic synthesist is not to be trifled with. Excellent aleatronic functionality, when and where it''s needed; 24 hours a day, every step of the mile. Includes secret sandwich compartment under secret door covered in pathetic technical scrawlings to deter even the most ravenous reader.</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(494, 59, 'TINFOILER ZERO', 500.00, 20.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iLSJr9rcx4w', ',,,,', 1, '<h1>Stop mind control dead with TINFOILER ZERO</h1>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Microwaves? Hah! </span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">HAARP got you down? No more! </span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">ELF detuning your DNA? Fret not! </span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Dishwasher giving you conflicting commands RE what to do about it all, finally? SHOW THEM WHO''S BOSS.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Yes. Once and for all the TINFOILER ZERO promises transcendence, liberty, AND freedom all in one attractive package, complete with comfort-inducing chin strap. Simply apply the TINFOILER ZERO, adjust, and enjoy the soothing wavelengths YOU CHOOSE to groove against authority. The built in oscillators, amplifier, filter, and FREEDOM FEEDBACK SYSTEM take care of the rest, effortlessly! Tired of the door-to-door harangue from itinerant pastafarians? They and all their ilk shall have no choice but to cower and bow before superior logic whenever the bearer of TINFOILER ZERO answers their call in the mother and father of all strainers in one, all across the land, for a thousand years.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Psychothermal flux technology:<br /><br />http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iLSJr9rcx4w<br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Recommended for use over a hat of some kind. <br /></span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 15, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(495, 38, '49-node All-Neon Hysteresis Relaxation Oscillator', 500.00, 20.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XWgMw9m9xzY ', ',,,,', 1, '<h1>FINALLY- A 49-node all-neon hysteresis relaxation oscillator for the nursery, den, or office.</h1>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">The magic of silence, and pareidolia, at a reasonable price! A grid of 49 neon lamps compete for a fixed amount of power, and hysteresis has something to do with it. The end product is a fascinating and endless parade of brain doodles. De/re/unprogram by letting quantum effects and population inversions in plasma directly soothe frazzled neural connections! This is a purely analog system, all gas, and it all glows. For that reason it''s probably not shower-safe. The case is missing a little rubber foot in the back corner, a condition present when salvaged from its former life as what is colloquially known as ''science juncque''. Sweet orange cord.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XWgMw9m9xzY </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(496, 34, 'Pocket AIR COMMANDER 50000000000000000000000000000', 400.00, 20.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0QGYzmENu3E', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">Everyone had resigned themselves to boredom some hours into that long flight to Beijing; but it was not to last, as you unzipped your only carry-on and positioned the Pocket AIR COMMANDER 5000000000000000000000000000000000000000 prominently on your lap, switched it on, and in an authoritative tone announced to all who cared to listen: ''THIS SITUATION IS UNDER CONTROL, LEAVE EVERYTHING TO ME, RELAX, GO ABOUT YOUR LIVES.''</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Yes, that life of intrigue and mystery that has always seemed just out of reach is, now, um, less just, um, out of reach. The Pocket AIR COMMANDER 5000000000000000000000000000000000000000 features a little joystick and some switches on the top, complimented by nice pink/purple LEDs, that light up. Flipping the unit over reveals some photosensors and some multicolor LEDs that shimmy shimmy yeah when the joystick is pushed inwards. There''s an audio out jack, little internal speaker, and nice EZ-GRIP handles for moments of clear-air turbulence. Commandingly statist olive green, black, and chrome color scheme.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The Pocket AIR COMMANDER 5000000000000000000000000000000000000000 also makes little synthy noises. PLL VCO and bandpass filter. 9V battery makes it, and by extension, all that is good; go.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0QGYzmENu3E </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 15, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(497, 152, 'BOP GUN', 1200.00, 20.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TXuqqpI03R4 ', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">Finally the conundrum of the universes'' missing funk has an answer: BOP GUN.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">5 mixed squarewave oscillators allow for rapid phase matching and total funky collapse of even the most complex wave functions!</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">LFO modulates filter! All oscillators, LFO and filter are controlled by global attack/decay functions at the pull of a trigger! INVERT function allows for continuous function for those situations requiring fancy long-term funkic interventions. Funkify traffic! Passers-by! Bar Mitzvahs! The sky!</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">LED feedback ring at the business end reacts to funk levels, providing photonic enhancement in attractive aqua green tones. Extra-sweet readout panel provides incomprehensible feedback from selected functions. Audio output jack included, and batteries fit in the handle.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Brief, cretinous vidayo exposition here:</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TXuqqpI03R4 </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 1),
(498, 32, 'Subaqueous HUMOR the strings of 1989', 600.00, 20.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NFsA5b9rCdk', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">As the pressure reached equilibrium and the condensation cleared, Dr. Wincehauer noticed something beyond the obvious treasures from throughout Greater Time that gleamed in the darkness of the vault, formerly Argon-filled and impenetrable, there deep in that salt dome, emplaced at some point in the hoary past by agencies unknown, intended to imperceptibly sink over geologic timescales to unfathomable depths and purpose; but in gasp and darkness of Argon-snuffed torches and the fumble for artificial light, somehow what then so fleetingly teased his attention was gone at the return of their fitful and disorganized attempts at lighting. The lascars had pilfered it, or one of the interns, there at the end of that long fatal tunnel in that Persian salt mine.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Or it had never existed in the first place, a trick of the eyes or cave-addled mind; as any reasonably skeptical person would understand, after all, how could an admittedly pretty cool 80s style single-voice pseudo-electric electronic guitar find its way into a secret hidden vault of secrets uncovered by a fictional cryptoarchaeologist in some sort of salt mine in Persia in the early part of the 1900s? Not only that, but to have it modified for hyperlight travel by inscrutably intelligent fictional agents of the future? Rotary crunchifiers, master frequency divider, glitchy strum buttons, active bandpass filter, just like those to be used on the hyperzithers in the space bazaars of 3045 AD? Oh yes. It''s not what it has been, but what it will be, there in the hyperfog machine smoke at the edge of the stage, peeling fat licks like some sort of space rock deity of the future.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A brief exposition of some of the added functionalities follows:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NFsA5b9rCdk</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">UPDATED for 2011!!! YES YES YES!!! Now jauntily sports ''theremin'' optical filter control, updated filter topology, continuously variable pitch control. Leading the pack in the ''89/''11 model year. </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(499, 35, 'VENGEANCE TWO', 500.00, 15.00, ' http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SdJz3t5kQnQ', ',,,,', 1, '<h1>VENGEANCE TWO because our parents still did not let us have keyboards</h1>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Quite possibly one of the most amazing and influential musical instruments ever devised. A valid demonstration that entirely novel combinations can arrive from simple starting points, modern technology has allowed us to finally embody Lucretian principles without resorting to so much stretched cat gut and cast bronze.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This video expounds a bit on the principles of the Lucretian cat-gutless Bendy Box principle, but prior to the development of Master Frequency Clock Pulse Generation as implemented in the final iteration:</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SdJz3t5kQnQ</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Simply turning this machine on, selecting an auto-rhythm, and mashing buttons places the synthesist behind the helm of their own veritable Starship Excelsior, exploring the glittering and sometimes muddy reaches of the Forbidden Zones, boldly. Saucily even, especially were one to find a sweet little rickety folding stand to pop under this thing. Not included. </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(500, 16, 'VENGEANCE ONE', 400.00, 15.00, ' http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HzGdZUX5MOU', ',,,,', 1, '<h1>VENGEANCE ONE because our parents never let us have keyboards.</h1>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Rumor has it that this very instrument was carefully sealed into a gold-sputtered kaplon envelope and tucked aboard voyager 1 and is presently somewhere near the discernible edge of the solar system, a missive from our species to the unknown. Luckily for us an engineer had smuggled out a precious bit of video footage, which would have been better had he not been using one hand to hold the camera, or remembered much from piano lessons.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HzGdZUX5MOU</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Our analysis of this bit of technology, symbolic of the aspirations of whoever happened to be around at the time to aspire, is that this device includes a master frequency control, a variable bandpass filter stage, and a very flexible system of circuit bend points, designed to appeal to a variety of theoretical sentient beings in their desire to tune the instrument to their liking, and thus smile on the earth, and not smite it into billions of molten fragments quite so flippantly. Truly, it''s an ambassador to the stars.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This device has been laboratory calibrated and certified for cross-species interplanetary communications efforts and funky getting down, up in the party. </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(501, 33, 'QUANTUM SYNTHESIS', 600.00, 15.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=irHTq9sQTlw', ',,,,', 1, '<h1>QUANTUM SYNTHESIS never sounded so good</h1>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Egregiously manipulating the fabric of space and time itself has never been easier! Simple, intuitive joystick control modulates a pair of oscillators, one of which provides fodder for an active bandpass filter that is modulated by the other. Switches and knobs allow for an endless variety of important combinations! In order to calibrate the stability of any resulting white/black holes, volume control and output jack are thoughtfully provided. Extra thoughtfully, now that we give it some thought, as there is no internal speaker. The iconic housing opens right up to reveal a horror of wires and boards, but as far as we can tell, it works, and works well, so no need to bother about in there and mess up the fine structure constant. The joystick is surrounded by multiple LEDs in what appears to be some binary encoded feedback system, the purpose of which currently eludes us.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">''A unique and impressive coracle from which to explore the endless shore with which this island of knowledge is bounded by the sea of mystery. Amaze your friends!''</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-Erasmus of Rotterdam, channeled by the Quantum Synthesizer</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A brief documentary can be found here: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=irHTq9sQTlw</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This is one of a special line of items that we specifically warrant to protect against ''alien invasion/abduction'' events. </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 15, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(502, 43, 'HELLMO', 350.00, 15.00, '', ',,,,', 1, '<h1>HELLMO lute of the valley of the hags</h1>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">That TV show so many children grew up with? Those characters? That Television workshop? A thousand generations ago, the ancient runes lining the waste of the forgotten valley spoke of those times, and of a spell that became possible only once in a thousand generations as the SPARK of a clock-hack, active bandpass filter and custom output stage meet the TINDER of carefully selected all-natural UV LEDs in a vessel, bearing the graven likenesses of those ghosts last smitten by the siren-song of the lute they only knew as HELLMO, for a thousand generations. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">''It takes the well-known string of tones programmed since childhood and melts them, freeing the mind, and all that follows.''</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-Albert Einstein, in an alternate universe.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The old man who bequeathed us this unfathomably ancient and powerful instrument spoke to us on his deathbed of an output jack, and yeah, for we found it, right there by the orange pickle thing. </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(503, 33, 'RIGNINGARDAGURKITTA', 250.00, 15.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aQk5n64VIx8', ',,,,', 1, '<h1>RIGNINGARDAGURKITTA: the lute of Bjork on rainy day</h1>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Humanely outfitted in pleasing and bright primary colors, RIGNINGARDAGURKITTA features ergodynamically correct clock (pitch) and active bandpass controls that can be switched from knob to OPTICAL THEREMIN control styles. A touch point, output jack, sustain control knob, and two-way overdrive switch round out the tasteful range of available options.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Whether entertaining bored courtesans as the blossoms fall in Edo period Japan, or playing heartstrings on a dark and rainy doorstop in iceland, RIGNINGARDAGURKITTA is like a ray of sunshine and a serving of freshly jugged herring. </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-16', 162, 5, 'manufacturer,,funding,,', '', 1, 0),
(504, 31, 'MJOLNIRSDOTTIR', 200.00, 15.00, '', ',,,,', 1, '<h1>MJOLNIRSDOTTIR, lute of the brazen bull</h1>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Translated fragment: ''It was none other than Thor himself, on that Tempest-wracked eve, who sang a paen of rage and love while his Fingers and Hands, scarred and sore with the travails of many Trials coaxed from MJOLNIRSDOTTIR a howling like the Banshees chained to the mighty doors of Hall Heorot, and thus lighting a fire in the hearts of the gathered Thanes.''</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Passed down through countless generations since the dawn of the epics themselves, this husk of a formerly hamstrung piffle of a toy guitar of uncertain manufacture has been graced with clock control (pitch) and an active bandpass filter (achieved via a vintage american-sourced opamp coupled to a custom output stage), both of which are controllable via vintage carefully hand-selected photoresistors, called by less scrupulous others at times THEREMIN, but not here; although both pitch and bandpass are controllable by hand shadows over the photoresistors, so perhaps in the future OPTICAL THEREMIN is not a too gratuitous stretching of the truth, as it were. Graciously added for your consideration is an output jack, so MJOLNIRSDOTTIR can be coupled to the thunder of 800 stacked tube amplifiers if so desired.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Stunningly appointed in carefully hand-selected black and white, with a nice aqua LED.</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-15', 162, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(508, 58, 'Mega man Laptop computer case suitcase', 190.00, 10.00, '', 'nintendo megaman, maga man,retro gamer NES,attache case geeky, geekery', 1, '<p>Mega man is one of my favorite characters, and here''s your chance to take him on your daily journey. This is great for storing your laptop (15" or smaller--pc shown is 17" to prove this point) or favorite items. Can be used as a briefcase, laptop attache case, storage box, wall art (though I really hope you actually use it), or an overnight suitcase.&nbsp;<br /><br />Details: Case is made mainly of thin, lightweight wood--in other words, this is not a toy. Please treat this case as you would a designer bag--with care. The outer shell of the case was painted with gray outdoor and acrylic paints, so even when it sprinkles, the paint remains in tact--however do not submerge case in water. Case is decorated in the style of megaman (NES) and his power bullets , overlayed with liner to give a smooth finish and longevity. Handle was made using rubber and shiny blue keyrings to accentuate mega man''s features, with recycled reusable bag cloth sewn inside for support. Faux rabbit fur is installed with flat tacks to protect interior items. Please do not tug at fur--underneath is paint and duct padding to give smoothness over bolts. Suitcase is not stompe-proof material, since wooden frame is not very thick. Remember this is handmade, hand-painted, hand-decorated, so brackets, alignment may be imperfect due to hardness of wood or error. Paint may have imperfections, though that''s what makes this one-of-a-kind. While the laptop doesn''t come with the case, I wanted to illustrate that a 17" laptop (shown) will be an uncomfortable fit. 15" etc should be fine, with extra room. This case is great for traveling, but do not check it, since the frame is made of 1/2 inch wood and would be best as carry on (you never know what luggage they can throw on your case). Note suitcase is actually light gray with cream fur (may look lighter in sunlight). Exterior is ~ 15.5" long, 12" tall (without handle), 3.25" wide. I added thin padding (electrical tape) to the latches to give a more secure and comfortable close: see latches in last photo (they feel like rubber, but it''s expandable tape). Thanks for checking out my work! :) If you have reservations about the imperfections that come with this recycled, handmade product, please email me before your purchase so I can respond :)</p>', 0, '2011-07-19', 168, 8, ',,,,', '<p>Will be insured with delivery confirmation. USA shipping only (domestic mail only)</p>', 1, 0),
(507, 44, 'Loudspeaker 4', 119.00, 0.00, '', 'loudspeaker,surround,cinema,hi-fi,music', 99, '<div id="post-9" class="post-9 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized author-marko">\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;">Features:</h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">Small size (12 x 12 x 14 cm), aluminium alloy enclosure</span></h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">50W AES, 4ohms,&nbsp;full-range (90Hz-21kHz (internal hi-pass filter)</span></h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">91dB/W/m, 110&deg; angle coverage, arrayable (line-array option)</span></h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">Lightweight (1,5kg),&nbsp;Speakon input</span></h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">Black color, optional RAL color design</span></h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">Easy installation</span></h2>\n<p><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;"><br /></span></p>\n</div>\n<div class="entry-content">\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;">Applications:</h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">Line-array (4+ pieces) with&nbsp;8-12&Prime;sub-woofer (PA &amp; HI-FI)</span></h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">Side-fill for fixed PA system installations</span></h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">Surround &nbsp;side&amp;back unit (small PA and home cinema systems)</span></h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">Small control monitor</span></h2>\n<h2 class="entry-title" style="text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: normal;">Background music systems (restaurants, clubs, museum, theatre)</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\n</div>', 1, '2011-07-18', 163, 15, ',distributor,,,', '<p>Free in EU, 19$ rest of the world.</p>', 1, 0),
(509, 64, '4GB Green Lantern USB Flash Drive Mac PC laptop', 54.00, 8.00, '', 'geekery, geeky,USB flash drive,macbook pro computer accessory gadget mac, pc', 1, '<p>Transport the green lantern minifigure from computer to computer in a rocket, spaceshuttle, robot, or whatever suits your imagination. Machinery was used to insert components for a 4GB memory stick that is low enough to dock the manufacturer''s USB port for any laptop. Shown is a Macbook pro, where the neon yellow/green usb lights up in Green (lantern) flashes when initially docked and when removed (into trash) :) As seen in images one through five, the building blocks can be made in to several types of shuttles where the shuttle door opens and closes to seat a miniature green lantern super hero with posable arms (perfect for the stickshift). The USB is designed to accommodate fit any mac (os 10.4 and up) or PC computer, and stores 4 GB of data.<br /><br />While pieces were originally manufactured by trio, they were manipulated with machinery, so the USB figure piece may have imperfections. See figure 4 lower left panel for USB block, and figure 1. The completed USB block will have small pieces of rubber tape, mainly for superficial purposes and to remind you to refrain from trying to pull the green block from the black one. USB block appears as ROCKETDRIVE on your computer, see figure 5 and will have varying amounts of electrical tape, adhesive and polish, if any. USB blocks have been sealed shut with industrial adhesive to for safety. These are the only two blocks that are sealed shut. The rest are free to move and reconstruct into unique projects. I''ve shown three styles of spaceships here, so please let me know if you''d like this shipped in either form, robot, spaceshuttle large, or narrow spaceshuttle (final figure). I will include a few extra blocks that will come with your kit for your imaginative adventure. This is the PERFECT gift for any comic book fan, geek, nerd or anyone who enjoys kids toys. I can also send them in pieces if you like. Note---while these pieces were originally made for kids, this set up is NOT a toy, and is meant for adult use with a computer. Please contact me if you have reservations about possible flaws before you purchase this very very cool gift (you can get this for friends, but no one will know if you keep it :) I would. PS. laptop will not come with purchase, which will include the blocks and the mini figure :)<br /><br />Adjacent to computer, the built spaceship measures 10" wide and 10" out from the laptop, standing 4.5" tall. Image one is a bit wider at 12" wingspan and just under 10" long. The robot MY FAVE measures 10" wide wingspan, 8" tall, and projects out 6.5" from the computer. Again these can be changed based on how you want to construct your own transporter! There are no laser sounds or animations¬†of the blocks with this kit, however the shuttle door opens and closes. Thanks for looking! :)</p>\n<div id="item-shipping" class="section">¬†</div>', 0, '2011-07-20', 168, 5, ',,,,', '<p>this is for USA domestic insured shipping only.¬†</p>', 1, 0),
(512, 49, 'Nintendo NES controller mini case purse', 56.00, 10.50, '', 'gamer purse,bag gadget,artwork box,handbag industrial,video game art', 1, '<h1>TA-DA. the nintendo-inspired mini controller case. Take your nintendo everywhere you go with this nostalgic retro case. The NES case measures approximately 7" long, just under 5" tall (minus the handle), and app 3" wide. This bag/purse is painted with outdoor paint (to make it rainproof, though purse is not submersible in water)--nothing will happen to the paint when it sprinkles. The frontside controller was made with acrylics sealed with shelf liner to preserve the surface. The back features an NES design made of red fabric/laces and electrical tape, also sealed with contact liner to preserve design. This case was made by recycling thin, unfinished wood. Although this is not a toy, please handle with care as you would any designer purse. The inside is lined with doubled faux rabbit fur that feels incredibly soft. This fur was installed with flat tacks to protect interior items. Please do not remove faux fur or tacks--underneath is the same exterior paint with duct padding over bolts for comfort. The handle is made from recycled bike parts, keyrings, galvanized pipe, heavy duty chains, and a silicone grip that can be easily cleansed with a soapy sponge. Since I''m a fan of industrial design, the purse was made with brackets and braces to keep you in the times despite your NES nostalgia. USE EITHER SIDE AS THE FRONT!<br /><br />note this is a handmade one-of-a-kind functional art piece. it will have imperfections, including uneven paint, alignment, brackets due to hardness of wood and error, but that''s what makes it unique. it''s the only one in the world. If you have reservations about the imperfections that come with this recycled, handmade product, please email me with any question. Thank you.</h1>', 0, '2011-07-20', 168, 8, ',,,,', '<p>domestic shipping only USA</p>', 1, 0),
(510, 82, 'Batman 4GB flash drive recycled Lego mini figure ', 55.00, 5.00, '', 'batman dark knight,recycled comics comic book dc superhero super hero,electronic geeky nerdy gadget USB 4GB memory stick,upcycled lego flash drive thumb drive,supeheroes', 1, '<p>Trust your most protected files to the caped crusader, who is equipped to store 4GB of memory.&nbsp; Batman is compatible with any laptop or desktop pc or mac (i believe OS 10.4 or higher).&nbsp; Unlike the his dynamic duo accomplice, Batman is posable! You can turn his head, arms, all but his legs.&nbsp; Batman was previously issued as a single, solid lego toy by mcdonald''s.&nbsp; His body was manipulated with machinery so that his legs are detachable, and a space was created to incorporate small USB components.&nbsp; Please note this is a handmade product, and will have imperfections.&nbsp; The USB stick fits perfectly into his pants, and some will stick out underneath (see all figures) because the the hole in his pants is NOT SEALED (the usb stick is visible when you flip him upside down, etc). Note also batman must lay on his abs for you to plug him into your laptop (he will fit the manufacturer''s USB port without any extension chords--see final image, where once plugged in, you will see a 4GB "BATMAN" icon on your desktop.&nbsp; Images were taken with a Macbook, which is not included with your batman :). Because this is a recycled, previously used toy, the USB stick will have imperfections--scratches from previous use and machinery, etc.&nbsp; It''s fully functional, but please consider this is no longer a toy--treat it with care, since the USB stick is very thin and fragile, like all ministicks. <span>Batman is 3.25" from head to feet, 2.5" from arm to arm, and 1.6" from abs to the rear cape. </span>If you wish to give Batman company, I can offer the dynamic duo pair for $80 and waive shipping (you will save close to $15).&nbsp; But you must tell me before hand, so I can set up a special listing for you.&nbsp; This is the perfect gift for any batman or superhero fan, and it''s usable, providing comic relief with functionality :) Thanks for visiting my project.</p>', 0, '2011-07-19', 168, 5, ',,,,', '<p>shipping is for USA only. will include delivery confirmation and insurance.</p>', 1, 1),
(511, 44, 'The Bat Stick 4GB Batman Mini Batmobile Superhero ', 42.00, 5.00, '', 'batstick bat-stick, batman, darknight,superhero, super hero batmobile 4GB memory stick,memory flash thumb drive,recycled lego dc comics comic book,geeky gift', 1, '<p>Allow Batman to protect your most valued documents with this "bat-stick" with 4GB memory. This little collector''s piece was designed by making a rectangular opening in a batman lego mini mobile (issued by mcdonalds), and attaching components for a flash drive. Note memory stick is very thin, and though it comes with a small protective rubber handmade muzzle, please use with care, since this is not a toy. Since this was a used toy (initially), and the plastic was manipulated with machinery, after sealant was applied, edges of the mini bat mobile have been covered with rubber tape for a smooth look that blends decently with the plastic. This memory stick will work with any computer--shown is a mac laptop. When docked, mini bat-stick protrudes 2.5 inches from the usb hub or computer. The wing width is approximately just over 1.5". USB drive will appear as "bat-stick" on your screen. Please don''t hesitate to contact me with further questions. If you need a larger USB, I most likely can try to accommodate your needs.&nbsp;<br /><br />this is a HANDMADE, recycled used toy converted into a flash drive. Imperfections range from scratches from prior use (remember I recycled this toy), and machinery-induced scratches. Please consider that this is one of a kind, and even if I replicate this piece, it will be slightly different. The one you''re buying is the exact one in the photos. Once more, you are purchasing a handmade recycled piece of functional art--this will have imperfections (see above). If you should have reservations about this recycled, handmade product, please email me before your purchase so I can answer your questions. Cheers :)</p>\n<p>Also, since the USB did not come with a cap, remember I recycled everything, I had to construct one out of rubber tape and cardboard--I added a gotham city batsticker that I think looks very cool for the muzzle of the mini batstick.&nbsp;</p>', 0, '2011-07-19', 168, 5, ',,,,', '<p>domestic USA shipping only. please contact me for international orders.</p>', 1, 0);
