(513, 65, 'Nintendo Controller Laptop Case NES Briefcase ', 180.00, 15.00, '', 'gamer bag case suitcase,macbook pro laptop accessory pc mac,video game videogame ,handmade,art', 1, 'Control your coworkers and friends by pressing buttons for how high they jump, lmao. kidding. Make any adventure a video game with the controller attache case. \n\nDetails: This case is handmade from thin, lightweight wood. The attache case was painted with outdoor paint and acrylics, so rain will not tamper with paint, however do not submerge case in water. Controller design was covered in contact liner for surface protection. Handle is made with super rubber and shiny red keyrings to accentuate the NES red features, using recycled reusable bags that were sewn together for support. The interior faux rabbit feels SO GOOD and is held together by both flat tacks and screws to avoid damaging contents. Please do not tug at rabbit fur--underneath is the same paint as the exterior with duct padding over bolts for a smooth finish. Do not treat suitcase like stompe-proof material, because recycled wooden frame is not very thick. Remember this is handmade, hand painted, hand decorated, hand assembled, etc--the alignment may not be perfect, brackets, latches and the paint may have imperfections due to hardness of wood and man-made error--but that''s what makes this one-of-a-kind. Laptop doesn''t accompany purchase, though I''ve included the image to prove a 17" laptop (shown) is NOT recommended for this case. Laptops 15" or smaller will be fine. Also, this case is great for traveling, but do not check it as the frame is made of 1/2 inch wood and would be best as carry on (you never know what luggage they can throw on). Suitcase is light gray, with gray faux fur inside. Exterior roughly 15.5" long, 12" tall (without handle), 3.25" wide. I added thin padding (electrical tape) to the latches to give a more secure and comfortable close. See last photo (they feel like rubber, but it''s stretchable tape). If you have reservations about the imperfections that come with this recycled, handmade product, please email me before purchase so I can respond!', 0, '2011-07-20', 168, 8, ',,,,', '<p>USA domestic shipping only. please contact me for international orders. shipping is insured with tracking.¬†</p>', 1, 0),
(515, 23, 'Luna Cube - Light controlled Synthesizer', 195.00, 13.30, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yH8HozNHkf8', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The Luna Cube is a small hand held synth that uses light to make a large range of electronic noises.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The light sensor inputs allow you to get a full range of sounds very quickly, they work as fast a you can move your fingers across the sensors. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">If you want to hear what the Luna Cube sounds like, I have upload a small YouTube video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yH8HozNHkf8</span><br /> <br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Main controls:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Pitch: the pitch control allows you to make, 127 tones and 127 white noise variations using the right hand light sensor as an input. For crazy effect use a small LED torch that has a strobe function.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Chopper: The chopper control changes the frequency of the sound up and down. The speed of these changes is dependent on left hand side light sensor. The more light that enters the sensor the faster the sound moment, until the point where sound is chopped up. </span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 1/4" mono socket which can be plugged into headphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">I hope that gives you a basic idea about how the Luna Cube works, if you have any questions please feel free to convo me.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy noise making,</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">RareBeasts </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '<p>Shipping to US 13.30</p>\n<p>Australia 8.80</p>\n<p>Everywehre Else 17.70</p>', 1, 0),
(514, 39, 'Clandestine DESKTOP UMPHERPHONE', 1750.00, 50.00, '', ',,,,', 1, '<p>The iconic and very very analog Clandestine Umpherphone. Little more needs to be said in the way of introducing this old chestnut. Classic functions just the way everyone remembers from the good old days, and that unforgettable umpherphone sound: 3 crossmodulated squarewave oscillators feeding 2 active bandpass filters that are modulated out of phase by an LFO. So simple, yet so enduring. Like ancient Greece. Then, flip the switch and use the pressure pad to make the party electric, the Clandestine way!<br /><br />This Clandestine production prototype is appointed in acrylic and a variety of comfortable aluminum knobbery and aforementioned pressure pad. Includes 110V power jack, and audio output.<br /><br />This holiday season, remember the homeworld together with a stout family umpherphonic degarbifulation delivered the way only Clandestine delivers: with love.</p>', 0, '2011-07-19', 162, 5, 'manufacturer,,funding,,', '', 1, 0),
(516, 36, 'Limited edition Mollusc Minds cassette', 12.00, 12.30, '', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">This is a limited edition 90 minute cassette self release from my band Cup and Bow. </span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">You can listen to a sample of this album here: http://cupandbow.bandcamp.com/album/mollusc-minds</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">About the Music: This album explores experimental music from dark drones, soft strings and harsh noise. All of the instruments played on this album are handmade by cup and bow</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Side A includes the 8 tracks from the Mollusc Minds album.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Side B includes a 45 minute live performance recorded in Canberra in June 2011.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Included is the Cassette tape, cassette cover and handmade inlay which includes the front cover artwork and pictures of each of the hand made instruments played on the album.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The artwork on the cassette is the front panel artwork from the R-Drone, the main instrument used on the album.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The instruments played on this album are available in my Broodr shop. </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 1, ',,,,', '<div id="cboxLoadedContent" style="display: block; width: 840px; overflow: auto; height: 124px;">\n<div id="shipping-popup">\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Shipping to US 13.30</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Australia 8.80</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Everywehre Else 17.70</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>', 1, 0),
(517, 32, 'MoofTronic -- worlds smallest synth', 89.00, 9.90, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U3cZBj7ZKZY', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">MoofTronic - Miniature Electronic Synth</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Looking for the new sound? Make some noise with this miniature synthesiser that uses a stylus to play 8 different notes.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Check out this YouTube video of the Mooftronic in action: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U3cZBj7ZKZY</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">With the mini synth you use a stylus to play sounds(one octave in the key of C). It also has a small antenna that when touched, controls the modulation span of the note being played. It creates a fast modulation LoFi type sound, that makes some crazy noises when the antenna picks up interference created by the output of the speaker. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">It measures about 3cm x 1cm and is based around a 24pin ic holder. The notes are generated by software programmed onto a Picaxe 08M microcontroller which has a small speaker mounted on it. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This device is handmade by me and 100% my design.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">* Item shipped from Australia, all prices are in US$.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">* The Mooftronic is powered by a Common 9v Battery which is not included due to shipping restrictions.</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy Noise Making</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">RareBeasts</span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '<p>Outside US $11.90</p>', 1, 0),
(524, 69, 'Wicks Looper - make experimental ambient drone mus', 119.00, 16.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w4mP25Mxuv0', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The Wicks Looper is a small electronic musical instrument that allows you the create real-time noise loops and sound effects. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Catch the Looper in action here on Youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w4mP25Mxuv0</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;">Using the tempo, sound and write controls, you can quickly build up build up sound loops in real time .</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The wicks looper has 3 main controls; </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The sound control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This control adjusts the frequency of the tone in the first half of the dial and the level of noise in the second half of the dial, giving two distinct sounds.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The tempo control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The second control is Tempo, which controls how fast the loop is played. Write the loop at a slow tempo then speed it up for a great effect. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The write control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The third control is the write button, when pressed it writes a sound to memory which is then replayed next time the loop is run. With the sound control knob adjusted anticlockwise, you can add a rest to the loop by pressing the Write button.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 3.5mm stereo socket which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">*Note: Headphones not included.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Don''t hesitate to convo me with questions or requests.</span><br /> <br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy noise making... </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 1),
(518, 33, 'R-Drone Station - Naked', 119.00, 16.50, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cBHiKGNMx6s', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">Just like the original R-Drone Station without the front panel print. I did this as a custom order and liked the look of the minimal black front panel.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The R-Drone Station is a small electronic musical instrument that allows you to create deep drone loops at various frequencies and speeds. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Catch the R-Drone in action here on Youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cBHiKGNMx6s</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;">Use the Freq and D-Level controls to build up super fast loops or slow drones, that can last for up to 48 hours(limited only by the life of the 9v battery) . </span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The R-Drone Station has 3 main controls; </span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The Freq control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This control adjusts the frequency of the tone in the first half of the dial and the level of noise in the second half of the dial, giving two distinct sounds.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The D-Level control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This control adjusts how deep the drone is played. With this control CW only one sound layer is played, as the knob is moved to the left the sounds are added in layers. As layers are added the drone gets deeper and the speed of the loop is also reduced.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The write control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The third control is the write button, when pressed it writes a sound to memory which is then replayed next time the loop is run. With the sound control knob adjusted anticlockwise, you can add a rest to the loop by pressing the Write button.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 3.5mm stereo socket which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The R-Drone Station runs on a 9v battery. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Don''t hesitate to convo me with questions or requests.</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy noise making... </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(519, 23, 'EM-Tronic - Wooden noise synth', 104.00, 16.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xm2K51MhHh8', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The EM-Tronic is a small hand held synth that makes a large range of electronic noises.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">If you want to hear what the EM-Tronic sounds like, I have uploaded a small YouTube video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xm2K51MhHh8</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">With the combination of pitch, speed and mode controls, giving endless combination of sounds this Synthesizer packs quite a punch for it''s size.</span><br /> <br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Main controls:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Pitch: the pitch control allows you to make, 127 tones and 127 white noise variations.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Speed: The speed control has different functions depending on what mode is set, but essentially, it sets the time a tone or tones are played and repeated. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Mode: the EM-Tronic has three modes, mode 1 is basic and gives a bleep at the pitch and duration you set. mode 2 is delay mode, this mode gives a delay effect as you move the pitch control up and down. Mode three includes a delay and multiple notes played rapidly.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 3.5mm stereo socket which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">All you need to start making sounds, is a pair of earphones and a common 9 volt battery.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">I hope that gives you a basic idea about how the EM-Tronic works, if you have any questions please feel free to convo me. You can also follow me on twitter, for updates on my products: http://twitter.com/Rarebeasts </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy noise making,</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">RareBeasts </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(520, 28, 'Wicks Looper - Acid Mix - Synth loops', 119.00, 16.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LnZTQbs69Ps', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The Wicks Looper - Acid Mix is a small handmade device that allows you the create very fast noise loops, by adding layers of sound in real time.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Before I go into the details here is a short YouTube video showing the Wicks Looper in action: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LnZTQbs69Ps</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The wicks looper has 3 main controls; The frequency control adjusts the frequency of the noise, the first half of the range is tame, the 2nd half is uncut noise. The second control is Speed, which controls how fast the loop is played. The right hand side of this control plays the loop, forwards, turn the control to the left and the loop will play in reverse. Write the loop at a slow tempo then speed it up and reverse it, for a great effect. The third control is the write button, when pressed it writes a sound to memory which is then replayed next time the loop is run. With the Freq control knob adjusted anticlockwise, you can add a rest to the loop by pressing the Write button.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 3.5mm stereo socket which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">* The Wicks Looper Acid - Mix is powered by a Common 9v Battery which is not included due to shipping restrictions.</span><br /><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Q: What is the difference between the normal Wicks Looper and the Wicks Looper - Acid Mix?</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A: The Acid Mix version plays loops about 4 times faster by making the sound played very short, it gives a ruff, out of control sound. The Acid Mix will also plays loops in reverse.</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy noise making,</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Rarebeasts </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(521, 27, 'R-Drone Station - Drone Synth', 119.00, 16.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cBHiKGNMx6s', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The R-Drone Station is a small electronic musical instrument that allows you to create deep drone loops at various frequencies and speeds. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Catch the R-Drone in action here on Youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cBHiKGNMx6s</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;">Use the Freq and D-Level controls to build up super fast loops or slow drones, that can last for 48 hour(limited only by the life of the 9v battery) . </span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The R-Drone Station has 3 main controls; </span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The Freq control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This control adjusts the frequency of the tone in the first half of the dial and the level of noise in the second half of the dial, giving two distinct sounds.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The D-Level control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This control adjusts how deep the drone is played. With this control CW only one sound layer is played, as the knob is moved to the left the sounds are added in layers. As layers are added the drone gets deeper and the speed of the loop is also reduced.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The write control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The third control is the write button, when pressed it writes a sound to memory which is then replayed next time the loop is run. With the sound control knob adjusted anticlockwise, you can add a rest to the loop by pressing the Write button.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 3.5mm stereo socket which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The R-Drone Station runs on a 9v battery. </span><br /><br /