(528, 31, 'EM-Tronic - Handmade Synthesizer', 104.00, 16.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xm2K51MhHh8', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The EM-Tronic is a small hand held synth that makes a large range of electronic noises.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">If you want to hear what the EM-Tronic sounds like, I have uploaded a small YouTube video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xm2K51MhHh8</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">With the combination of pitch, speed and mode controls, giving endless combination of sounds this Synthesizer packs quite a punch for it''s size.</span><br /> <br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Main controls:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Pitch: the pitch control allows you to make, 127 tones and 127 white noise variations.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Speed: The speed control has different functions depending on what mode is set, but essentially, it sets the time a tone or tones are played and repeated. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Mode: the EM-Tronic has three modes, mode 1 is basic and gives a bleep at the pitch and duration you set. mode 2 is delay mode, this mode gives a delay effect as you move the pitch control up and down. Mode three includes a delay and multiple notes played rapidly.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 3.5mm stereo socket which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">I hope that gives you a basic idea about how the EM-Tronic works, if you have any questions please feel free to convo me.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy noise making,</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">RareBeasts </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(529, 26, 'DA-Synth - Simple Addictive Synth Beats', 180.00, 18.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WB3t_zx3a0I', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The DA-Synth is a small experimental handmade synth with a mode for making glitchy beats.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">If you want to hear what the DA-Synth looks and sounds like, I have uploaded a small YouTube video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WB3t_zx3a0I</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Main controls:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Pitch: the right knob controls the pitch of the device.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Sweep: The left knob controls the sweep of the device.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Mode: The switch on the left of the device controls the mode, the down position is basic synth mode which gives you pitch and sweep control. The up position is beat mode, in this mode you can take the sound set up in synth mode and turn it into a beat that is controlled by the number of bass notes(left control) and the speed of the beat(right control) </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 3.5mm stereo socket which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">All you need to start making sounds, is a pair of earphones and a common 9 volt battery.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">I hope that gives you a basic idea about how the DA-Synth works, if you have any questions please feel free to convo me. You can also follow me on twitter, for updates on my products: http://twitter.com/Rarebeasts </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy noise making,</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">RareBeasts </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(530, 27, 'Wicks Looper - The perfect musical gift', 119.00, 16.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w4mP25Mxuv0', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The Wicks Looper is a small electronic musical instrument that allows you the create real-time noise loops and sound effects. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Catch the Looper in action here on Youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w4mP25Mxuv0</span><br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;">Using the tempo, sound and write controls, you can quickly build up build up sound loops in real time .</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The wicks looper has 3 main controls; </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The sound control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This control adjusts the frequency of the tone in the first half of the dial and the level of noise in the second half of the dial, giving two distinct sounds.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The tempo control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The second control is Tempo, which controls how fast the loop is played. Write the loop at a slow tempo then speed it up for a great effect. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The write control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The third control is the write button, when pressed it writes a sound to memory which is then replayed next time the loop is run. With the sound control knob adjusted anticlockwise, you can add a rest to the loop by pressing the Write button.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 3.5mm stereo socket which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">*Note: Headphones not included.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Don''t hesitate to convo me with questions or requests.</span><br /> <br /> <br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy noise making... </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(531, 19, 'Crazy Looper - Great synth loops', 64.00, 16.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XrHkvvtrXhA', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The Crazy Looper is a small handmade device that allows you to create real-time noise loops with a fast modulation metallic effect.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Before I go into the details here is a short youtube video showing the Crazy Looper in action. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XrHkvvtrXhA</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The Crazy Looper builds up sound loops using three controls,tempo, sound and write. The sound control adjusts the frequency of the tone in the second half of the dial and the level of noise in the first half of the dial, giving two distinct sounds. The first half of the sounds have some spots that are blank to cut the sound up as you move the control up and down. The second control is Tempo, which controls how fast the loop is played. Write the loop at a slow tempo then speed it up for a great effect. The third control is the write LDR, when you put your finger over the light sensor it writes a sound to memory, which is then replayed next time the loop cycle starts. With the sound control knob adjusted clockwise, you can add a rest to the loop by pressing the Write button.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 3.5mm stereo socket which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">* Item shipped from Australia, all prices are in US$.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">* The Crazy Looper is powered by a Common 9v Battery which is not included due to shipping restrictions.</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy Shopping</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">RareBeasts </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(532, 30, 'SpinTronic - Light operated electronic musical ins', 295.00, 16.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0f5ps1t3Wgo', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The Spintronic is a light controlled electronic musical instrument, that makes a range of sounds by rotating wooden pin wheels.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Before I go into the details here is a short youtube video showing the SpinTronic in action. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0f5ps1t3Wgo</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Pin wheels are used to control the amount of light entering the sensors, one controlling frequency and the other, modulation. Three pin wheels are provided with this device.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A speaker is mounted in the SpinTronic and a 3.5mm stereo output is also provided for recording and amplification. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The SpinTronic''s brain is a small picaxe micro-controller mounted on the under side of the unit. This micro makes it''s sounds, from the varying electrical signal produced by the two LDR''s(light dependent resistors) mounted in the unit. The signals are processed by the micro and a stereo sound output is produced. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The SpinTronic is made from Recycled wood and finished in natural beewax. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">* Item shipped from Australia, all prices are in US$.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">* The SpinTronic is powered by a Common 9v Battery which is not included due to shipping restrictions.</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy Shopping</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">RareBeasts </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(533, 25, 'Master Looper - Make modulated sound loops', 149.00, 15.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_AGYKaHpoDg', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The Master Looper is a fully portable music synth, that allows you the create real-time noise loops and sound effects at hi speeds.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Youtube video of the Master Looper in action. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_AGYKaHpoDg</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This instrument will allow you to build up a sound loop in real time using the tempo, sound and write controls.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The Master looper has 3 main controls:</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The sound control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This control adjusts the frequency of the tone in the first half of the dial and the level of noise in the second half of the dial, giving two distinct sounds. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The Tempo control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The second control is Tempo, which controls how fast the loop is played . Write the loop at a slow tempo then speed it up for a great effect. In speed mode you can set the overall speed of the loop from x4 to x64, this makes for some very interesting noises.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The Write control:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The third control is the write button, when pressed it writes a sound to memory which is then replayed next time the loop is run. With the sound control knob adjusted anticlockwise, you can add a rest to the loop by pressing the Write button.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The stereo output is via a 1/4 inch socket, which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier.</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy noise making.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">RareBeasts </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(534, 24, 'DinoAxe - Mini Synth', 129.00, 16.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TB0uEySVqyU', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The DinoAxe makes noise, the noise is *weird*.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">DinoAxe Video http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TB0uEySVqyU</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This fun little device is a mini synth that uses two controls to make an interesting and diverse range of sounds.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The unit has two basic controls, Speed and Freq. The speed control has two functions; modulation and wobble. In Modulation mode the DinoAxe repeats the sound with a varying delay. In wobble mode the speed control varies the frequency in a sine wave pattern. The two functions are selected by rotating the speed control knob all the way counter clockwise. The Freq control varies the frequency of the sound, the first half of the control range is tones from low the high frequency, and the second part of the range is noise, noise, and more noise.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Batteries are fitted by removing a panel at the back of the unit, with a small screwdriver.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The output is via a 3.5mm stereo socket which can be plugged into earphones, a computer sound card, mixer or amplifier. I used a little vox amp in the video.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">* The DinoAxe is powered by a 9v Battery which is not included due to shipping restrictions.</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy noise making</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">RareBeasts </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(535, 31, 'StrobeTronic Noise-Lab', 475.00, 16.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fFjq0Sj7FXs', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">The StrobeTronic is a light controlled noise maker.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A short YouTube video at this link:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fFjq0Sj7FXs</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This unit makes a huge range of strange noises. You start by setting the controls on the top of the unit, this sets up a sweep on the LEDS, by moving the LEDs around the light sensors a basic noise loop is set up. Combinations of frequency, volume and the two LEDs make for interesting sounds.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The unit consists of three modules, 2 transmit and 1 receive. The transmit modules have 3 controls each, Sweep speed, sweep range and mode(sine wave, saw tooth and pulse). Each Tx module has a LED output attached to a flexible lead. The Receive module has two light sensors, one controls the frequency and the other volume.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The case of the unit is constructed from plastic tubes and wooden tops sealed using beeswax. </span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The unit is powered by a 9 volt battery which is not included due to shipping restrictions.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This device is handmade by me and 100% my design, its not made from a kit or found anywhere else.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Happy Shopping</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">RareBeasts </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 166, 5, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
(536, 51, 'Soothing blue animated LED lamp - light box', 150.00, 35.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zd032zjYgWk', 'blue,mood lamp,trippy,analog,led', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">Add some soothing electric art to your pad! Sure to be a conversation piece, this is a framed light sculpture from my "Electric Window 4" series of dynamic light fixtures. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Makes a perfect present for the geek w/ everything, an animated addition to contemporary condo decor, or a truly unique housewarming gift.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A grid of softly diffused blue LEDs organically displays undulating patterns based on random and sinusoidal wave functions. The pattern parameters cycle randomly, resulting in a serene, ever-evolving light display with a fluid, analog feel.</span><br /><br style="font-size: small;" /><span style="font-size: small;">For demonstration purposes, the above video shows the patterns shifting rapidly, but the actual piece cycles between speedy and slow modes for a varied personality. Also, although the video has a soundtrack, the piece does not make any sound. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Each piece is individually numbered and comes with a North American (120Vac) power supply. International orders are welcome, just contact me so I can determine which power supply you require.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">As shown in the last picture, which also shows an iPod (not included) for scale, other LED colors are also available, such as red, green, yellow, or white; just let me know your preference in your order comments.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This piece is ready to hang, or rest on a table or shelf. Simply plug it in and enjoy! It''s a mood lamp; an accent piece; a conversation starter; and a great way to enjoy digital art sans computer screen. It''s sure to supply a soothing ambiance to your surroundings.</span><br /><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">CUSTOMER REACTIONS</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">"I have gotten lots of positive comments about this light box and everyone loves it. Great artist."</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">"This is really great. I''m enjoying the light box a lot. It was shipped quickly and well and I highly recommend ordering one if you''re even halfway intrigued..."</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">"Wonderful art with LEDS. Finely crafted and fun to watch. At times - very zen. I am very pleased. Thank you."</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">DETAILED SPECS</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Title: "Electric Window (4.xx)"</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Materials: LEDs, custom electronics, acrylic panel, wooden enclosure</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Dimensions: 5" x 7" x 2"</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Power consumption: 2 watts (that''s right, it would take 30 of these to use the same energy as a 60W bulb!)</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Thanks for your interest!</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">OTHER TAGS</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">blue mood lamp</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">blue mood light</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">blue accent lamp</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">blue accent light</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">led mood lamp</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">led mood light</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">led accent lamp</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">led accent light </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 110, 15, 'manufacturer,distributor,funding,promotion,', '<p>Canada $10</p>\n<p>USA $15</p>\n<p>Australia $35</p>\n<p>Everywhere else $30</p>', 1, 0);
