(537, 198, 'Green animated LED lamp - light box', 150.00, 35.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EsJEEIn5SvY', 'green,led,lamp,light,pong', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">Add some dynamic, digital art to your pad! Sure to be a conversation piece, this is an "open concept" sculpture from my "Electric Window 3" series of dynamic light fixtures.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Makes a perfect present for the geek w/ everything, an animated addition to a contemporary condo, or a truly unique housewarming gift. Very cool for the office as well!</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">A green LED pixel panel illuminates with playful patterns based on autonomous drawing algorithms. Some of the patterns randomly fill the screen with geometric elements -- lines, boxes, etc. -- and others are inspired by 8-bit video game aesthetics, think <strong>Pong</strong> and <strong>Space Invaders</strong>! The patterns randomly cycle for random durations, resulting in an organic, ever-evolving light show.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Here''s some <strong>videos</strong> showing a few of the patterns:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://vimeo.com/11125903 [Matrix Rain]</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://vimeo.com/11125456 [PONG]</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://vimeo.com/8032267 [Space Invaders]</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">http://vimeo.com/7446509 [random patterns and drawing]</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">[ NOTE: the above videos show various versions of this light design as available in separate listings here; the programming is the same, however. Also, although some videos have soundtracks, the piece does not make any sound. ]</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The "open concept" enclosure allows full inspection of the hand-soldered circuit board. The 4th picture shows an iPod (not included) for scale. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Each piece is individually numbered and comes with a North American (120Vac) power supply. International orders are welcome, just contact me so I can determine which power supply you require.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">This piece is ready to hang, or rest on a table or shelf. Simply plug it in and enjoy! It''s a mood lamp; an accept piece; a conversation starter; and a great way to enjoy digital art away from the computer screen. It''s sure to add some intriguing ambiance to your surroundings.</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">DETAILED SPECS</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Title: "Electric Window (3.xx)"</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Materials: LED panel, custom electronics, acrylic panels</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Dimensions: 4.5" x 7.25" x 2"</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Power consumption: 2 watts (that''s right, it would take 30 of these to use the same energy as a 60W bulb!) </span><br /><br /></p>', 0, '2011-07-20', 110, 15, 'manufacturer,distributor,funding,promotion,', '<p>To Canada $10</p>\n<p>USA $15</p>\n<p>Australia $35</p>\n<p>Everywhere Else $30</p>', 1, 1),
(538, 31, 'MELODROMOTRON ALEATRON 1.0.1.1 updated', 1001.00, 50.00, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VGsdvYE9W4E', 'atari punk console,synth,analog,custom,visual', 1, '<p>Melodromatic aleatronity, at your fingertips! A revolutionary photonic optical feedback system and variable bandpass filter accompany a modified Atari Punk Console wrapped a comely, yet modest E-Z view display case with carrying handle. Handy reference grid included!<br /><br />With your hands hovering over the stately light sensitive controls of hand-hewn copper, the palpably writhing forces within this unit stand ready to execute your whim in the confident comfort and elegance that only painstakingly hand-crafted fake woodgrain can provide. Carefully selected orange knobs compliment an array of shimmering stainless switches and deep violet indicators in select vintage indicator housings.<br /><br />Features an expansive sample bay for shadow boxes, instructional cut-outs, miracle/mystery plays acted out by trained gerbils ''en silhouette'', etc. 110V cord and audio out jack.<br /><br />UPDATED FOR 2011! NEW AMP DESIGN! UPDATED FILTER CHIP! LED FEEDBACK AVAILABLE ON ALL CONTROLS! MADE ENTIRELY OF SOLID GOLD (NOT INTENDED TO BE A FACTUAL STATEMENT)</p>', 0, '2011-07-21', 162, 5, ',,funding,,', '', 1, 0),
