(620, 90, ' 8-Bit Heart in 14kt Yellow Gold', 270.00, 5.90, '', 'Jewelry,NES,Gold,Retro,Geek', 1, '<p>"Every bit of my heart."<br />This heart pendant is stylized after the pixelated artwork found in retro 8-bit video games. I wanted to emulate the digital nature of these old school graphics with their crisp and blocky edges, and to give the piece an even stronger appearance the surface of the heart is faceted to represent each individual pixel.<br /><br />The heart pendant is made of solid 14kt yellow gold and measures 15x15 mm. Chain not included.</p>', 1, '2011-07-25', 143, 1, 'manufacturer,distributor,,promotion,', '<p>All items are packaged in a gift box and shipped by USPS Priority Mail with a tracking number. Items will ship within two business days of purchase.</p>', 1, 0),
(622, 19, '2011 Photo Calendar Handmade 5x7', 22.00, 3.75, '', ',,,,', 1, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">This is a handmade 2011 calendar using original photos from my blueorder collection. Each photo was chosen for the corresponding month, while the first letter of each day is also matched with the overall color theme of the photograph.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The 4x6 photograph is then placed on a hand cut 5x7 black mat board. Each photograph is then secured in place by four pieces of black tape in each of the four corners.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Because these calendars are handmade my me, each calendar may show slight variations in cut and tape placement.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">I will supply one clip that can be used to hang one month at a time. However they can easily be tacked, taped or mounted in most places.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Note: I can also provide 4x6 photographs without the black mat board and tape for $12.00 with reduced shipping as well.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">For any questions please at all please convo me :)</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Calendar will be shipped using USPS First Class </span></p>', 0, '2011-07-25', 171, 11, ',,,,', '', 1, 0),
